1
00:00:18,177 --> 00:00:19,445
THE VILLAGE BARBER

2
00:00:27,086 --> 00:00:28,954
THE VILLAGE BARBER

3
00:00:30,890 --> 00:00:33,425
THEIR LONG-AWAITED DAY OFF ENDS

4
00:00:33,492 --> 00:00:36,562
AND IT'S YET ANOTHER MORNING OF WORK

5
00:00:40,933 --> 00:00:42,368
Let's go. I'm ready.

6
00:00:43,202 --> 00:00:47,039
THE TRIO IS FULLY RECHARGED
AFTER TAKING A DAY OFF

7
00:00:47,773 --> 00:00:50,776
- Do you need help with that?
- Hey, wait. We're dressed similarly.

8
00:00:51,544 --> 00:00:53,112
- Looking great.
- Pretty dope.

9
00:00:53,546 --> 00:00:55,347
Today's key color is red.

10
00:00:57,316 --> 00:00:59,585
I wonder what's waiting for us today.

11
00:00:59,652 --> 00:01:00,819
CURRENT TIME: 7:30 A.M.
THE TRIO LEAVE EARLIER THAN USUAL

12
00:01:00,886 --> 00:01:03,622
- What kind of customers await us?
- I wonder.

13
00:01:06,191 --> 00:01:07,893
How do you two even move in sync?

14
00:01:07,960 --> 00:01:09,194
LEFT, RIGHT

15
00:01:10,296 --> 00:01:12,598
- You know what? You're in sync, too.
- Yes.

16
00:01:12,665 --> 00:01:13,832
Really?

17
00:01:13,899 --> 00:01:15,134
The three of us are

18
00:01:15,868 --> 00:01:17,002
destined.

19
00:01:17,703 --> 00:01:20,306
This is what I call your destiny

20
00:01:20,372 --> 00:01:21,373
Do you know this song?

21
00:01:24,310 --> 00:01:28,347
WHY ARE THEY
GOING TO WORK THIS EARLY TODAY?

22
00:01:28,414 --> 00:01:29,682
The snow has mostly melted.

23
00:01:30,583 --> 00:01:31,584
They're mostly gone.

24
00:01:32,551 --> 00:01:35,454
ARRIVED 30 MINUTES EARLIER THAN USUAL

25
00:01:35,521 --> 00:01:38,057
All right. Let us start another day.

26
00:01:38,624 --> 00:01:42,895
LET'S GET READY TO OPEN

27
00:01:43,228 --> 00:01:44,830
Would you like to sit down first?

28
00:01:45,464 --> 00:01:47,733
DO THEY ALREADY HAVE A CUSTOMER
WHEN THEY JUST GOT TO WORK?

29
00:01:49,335 --> 00:01:51,670
WHY IS DONG-YEON SITTING DOWN
WEARING A CAPE?

30
00:01:51,737 --> 00:01:53,706
I have to keep this vibe

31
00:01:53,772 --> 00:01:56,475
but my hair does seem
a bit too long right now.

32
00:01:57,977 --> 00:01:59,044
EARLIER

33
00:01:59,111 --> 00:02:00,279
Boss PARK.

34
00:02:01,113 --> 00:02:02,715
Can you do my hair?

35
00:02:03,382 --> 00:02:06,051
Sure, I'd love to.
Let me have a glass of water first.

36
00:02:06,118 --> 00:02:07,319
HE ASKS BO GUM FOR A HAIRDO

37
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:09,955
HIS HAIR GREW OUT QUITE A LOT
DURING HIS STAY IN MUJU

38
00:02:10,022 --> 00:02:12,925
I'm a little torn.
Should I cut your hair or not?

39
00:02:13,659 --> 00:02:15,194
The thing is

40
00:02:15,260 --> 00:02:17,529
I don't know what your character
will be in your next project.

41
00:02:17,863 --> 00:02:19,832
- The length...
- Boss PARK.

42
00:02:20,766 --> 00:02:22,067
You never know.

43
00:02:22,134 --> 00:02:23,535
THAT'S WHY HE'S MORE TORN

44
00:02:23,602 --> 00:02:25,904
- Leave it to the boss.
- Let me put this here.

45
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:29,108
You don't want
your ears to show, right?

46
00:02:29,174 --> 00:02:31,410
I don't think
you can cut it that short.

47
00:02:31,477 --> 00:02:32,978
In my opinion

48
00:02:33,312 --> 00:02:35,881
the hair in the back is too long.

49
00:02:35,948 --> 00:02:38,083
I've been growing it out
without styling it.

50
00:02:38,150 --> 00:02:40,352
I feel like it sticks out
here and there.

51
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:42,755
You can do as you like.

52
00:02:43,088 --> 00:02:44,990
You practiced
men's haircuts like crazy

53
00:02:45,057 --> 00:02:46,892
back in those days.

54
00:02:48,127 --> 00:02:50,095
- I'll just thin it out.
- Okay.

55
00:02:50,162 --> 00:02:51,330
WILL HE DO A GOOD JOB
ON HIS FAVORITE BRO?

56
00:02:52,197 --> 00:02:54,299
GLANCES

57
00:02:55,034 --> 00:02:58,604
We might panic if a customer comes
while you're cutting my hair.

58
00:02:58,704 --> 00:02:59,772
That's true.

59
00:02:59,838 --> 00:03:00,839
SEARCHING

60
00:03:00,906 --> 00:03:02,107
BO GUM IS SEARCHING FOR SOMETHING

61
00:03:02,875 --> 00:03:04,009
What do you need?

62
00:03:04,076 --> 00:03:06,412
It's okay. You stay right there.

63
00:03:07,346 --> 00:03:10,349
THE EMPLOYEE FEELS
MORE UNCOMFORTABLE SITTING

64
00:03:13,052 --> 00:03:15,354
A FAMILIAR BREATHING SOUND
SUDDENLY RINGS

65
00:03:19,291 --> 00:03:21,326
Hey, Ms. Ra! It's Ms. Ra.

66
00:03:21,393 --> 00:03:22,795
- Where is she?
- She's here.

67
00:03:23,262 --> 00:03:24,863
RUNNING OUT

68
00:03:25,464 --> 00:03:26,565
CHUCKLING

69
00:03:26,932 --> 00:03:29,001
Why are you out here so early?

70
00:03:29,068 --> 00:03:30,369
She's here.

71
00:03:30,436 --> 00:03:32,104
HE HASN'T STARTED CUTTING

72
00:03:32,171 --> 00:03:33,639
- Goodness.
- Hello, Ms. Ra.

73
00:03:33,706 --> 00:03:34,707
RISING ABRUPTLY

74
00:03:35,274 --> 00:03:37,109
THEY SUDDENLY PANIC
AT MS. RA'S SUDDEN APPEARANCE

75
00:03:37,910 --> 00:03:40,512
- Hello, Ms. Ra.
- How have you been?

76
00:03:42,414 --> 00:03:44,116
THE 92-YEAR-OLD STUDENT
MS. RA OK-JA IS HERE

77
00:03:44,183 --> 00:03:45,751
Did your studies go well yesterday?

78
00:03:45,818 --> 00:03:47,352
Of course. I studied a lot.

79
00:03:48,153 --> 00:03:49,221
I did lots of homework.

80
00:03:49,621 --> 00:03:52,391
- Please have a seat.
- I studied everything I was told to.

81
00:03:52,725 --> 00:03:54,259
Ms. Ra.

82
00:03:54,326 --> 00:03:55,961
Would you like
something warm to drink?

83
00:03:56,662 --> 00:03:58,764
Sure. I'll take a cup of coffee
if you have some.

84
00:03:58,831 --> 00:04:00,165
Instant coffee mix?

85
00:04:00,232 --> 00:04:02,267
- The sweet kind?
- The instant coffee mix.

86
00:04:02,334 --> 00:04:03,502
I'll make it quick.

87
00:04:04,169 --> 00:04:05,370
Wait...

88
00:04:05,537 --> 00:04:07,139
RUNS WITHOUT TAKING THE CAPE OFF

89
00:04:07,706 --> 00:04:09,274
HE'S SO FUNNY

90
00:04:10,409 --> 00:04:12,578
CHEF KWAK PREPARES COFFEE IN A HURRY

91
00:04:12,644 --> 00:04:14,346
SWOOSH

92
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:21,520
BACK TO HIS JOB SMOOTHLY
WITH THE CUTTING CAPE ON

93
00:04:22,721 --> 00:04:26,658
KEEPING STEADY
WITH THE COFFEE IN HIS HAND

94
00:04:29,628 --> 00:04:32,831
FINISHED MAKING COFFEE SKILLFULLY

95
00:04:35,267 --> 00:04:36,635
Here's your coffee.

96
00:04:37,736 --> 00:04:40,305
DONG-YEON SITS BACK DOWN
WHILE THERE ARE NO CUSTOMERS

97
00:04:40,372 --> 00:04:41,473
Let's do this.

98
00:04:42,274 --> 00:04:44,943
- Now, open your book.
- Okay.

99
00:04:45,010 --> 00:04:46,912
Ms. Ra Ok-ja, open your book.

100
00:04:46,979 --> 00:04:48,313
Yes, okay.

101
00:04:48,814 --> 00:04:50,783
CHUCKLING

102
00:04:51,116 --> 00:04:54,453
- She's adorable.
- Yes, she is.

103
00:04:55,254 --> 00:04:58,957
HE QUICKLY BEGINS TO CUT

104
00:04:59,892 --> 00:05:03,028
FOCUSED

105
00:05:04,196 --> 00:05:07,633
When you get your hairdresser license

106
00:05:08,100 --> 00:05:09,535
what do you want to do first?

107
00:05:09,902 --> 00:05:11,403
I kind of want to try perms.

108
00:05:12,437 --> 00:05:15,440
I want to know how I can make

109
00:05:15,507 --> 00:05:18,210
different curls
using the hair rolling technique.

110
00:05:19,545 --> 00:05:23,515
What shapes will I make
when I get to use the technique?

111
00:05:24,416 --> 00:05:27,152
When I see you cutting people's hair

112
00:05:29,388 --> 00:05:31,323
I can sense a burden on you.

113
00:05:31,390 --> 00:05:35,027
At first, it was a bit of a burden.

114
00:05:35,093 --> 00:05:38,030
Even now,
I have it as I'm cutting yours.

115
00:05:38,096 --> 00:05:41,867
But in the process,
I slowly became a bit more confident.

116
00:05:41,934 --> 00:05:44,403
I'm starting to enjoy it
instead of feeling burdened.

117
00:05:52,211 --> 00:05:55,647
I shouldn't have made you work
this early in the morning.

118
00:05:55,714 --> 00:05:56,815
Don't say that.

119
00:05:57,950 --> 00:05:59,284
It's not like that.

120
00:06:00,185 --> 00:06:03,355
I'm grateful for your trust in me.

121
00:06:07,159 --> 00:06:10,429
FOR THE FIRST TIME
SINCE BO GUM CAME HERE

122
00:06:10,495 --> 00:06:16,401
HE'S CUTTING DONG-YEON'S HAIR
INSTEAD OF A LOCAL'S

123
00:06:17,970 --> 00:06:21,874
CAREFULLY CUTTING

124
00:06:21,940 --> 00:06:25,244
ONE STRAND AFTER ANOTHER

125
00:06:27,880 --> 00:06:29,448
TINY BITS

126
00:06:30,415 --> 00:06:33,352
HE DOES HIS BEST TO CUT HIS HAIR

127
00:06:33,785 --> 00:06:36,555
1 HOUR HAS PASSED

128
00:06:36,622 --> 00:06:38,056
Let me finish up now.

129
00:06:49,601 --> 00:06:52,638
BLOW-DRYING PASSIONATELY

130
00:06:54,006 --> 00:06:56,375
DOING HIS BEST

131
00:06:59,278 --> 00:07:02,447
ON THE OTHER HAND,
THE EMPLOYEE LOOKS A BIT TIRED

132
00:07:03,815 --> 00:07:06,118
HAGGARD

133
00:07:07,519 --> 00:07:08,754
Are you slowly getting tired?

134
00:07:08,820 --> 00:07:11,256
- No, I'm fine.
- Feel free to let me know.

135
00:07:15,994 --> 00:07:19,865
HE CONTINUES TO YAWN
DESPITE HIS WORDS

136
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:23,635
THE STYLING BEGINS

137
00:07:25,003 --> 00:07:28,173
- I'll style your hair so it matches
- Okay.

138
00:07:28,240 --> 00:07:30,876
- with what you're wearing today.
- I'll look forward to it.

139
00:07:32,511 --> 00:07:33,979
Do you want to slick your hair back?

140
00:07:34,579 --> 00:07:35,814
BOSS PARK WANTS
TO SLICK HIS HAIR BACK

141
00:07:35,881 --> 00:07:36,882
No?

142
00:07:37,716 --> 00:07:41,787
It might bother me if my hair
gets droopy while I'm working.

143
00:07:41,853 --> 00:07:43,655
So please just blow-dry
and divide it.

144
00:07:43,722 --> 00:07:44,790
I'll do that.

145
00:07:45,390 --> 00:07:47,893
You can do whatever you want.
I'll leave it up to you.

146
00:07:49,394 --> 00:07:51,296
Let me press the sideburns down.

147
00:07:54,232 --> 00:07:57,336
SETTING THE SIDEBURNS,
DONG-YEON'S BIGGEST CONCERN

148
00:07:59,004 --> 00:08:00,672
THOROUGHLY

149
00:08:05,410 --> 00:08:07,579
QUIET

150
00:08:08,647 --> 00:08:10,682
- Do you feel hot?
- No, I'm fine.

151
00:08:10,749 --> 00:08:14,953
IT'S TAKING
MUCH LONGER THAN HE THOUGHT

152
00:08:16,154 --> 00:08:20,359
AND BOSS PARK CONTINUES
TO STYLE HIS HAIR

153
00:08:20,425 --> 00:08:23,061
WITH LOVE FOR HIS EMPLOYEE

154
00:08:25,063 --> 00:08:28,567
THE HAIR IRON TOO?

155
00:08:28,967 --> 00:08:31,803
FULL OF PASSION

156
00:08:32,738 --> 00:08:36,274
- The section you wrote yesterday.
- Yesterday? I don't know.

157
00:08:36,541 --> 00:08:37,642
I did just a little.

158
00:08:37,709 --> 00:08:41,179
- You got to M.
- Yes. I guess I did a little here.

159
00:08:41,246 --> 00:08:43,815
I tried writing it down
instead of sitting around.

160
00:08:43,882 --> 00:08:47,085
When we meet someone,
we say "hello" like this, right?

161
00:08:47,152 --> 00:08:49,454
You have to teach me
my name in English.

162
00:08:49,521 --> 00:08:50,522
Let's do that, too.

163
00:08:50,589 --> 00:08:52,724
It's Tamako in Japanese.

164
00:08:52,791 --> 00:08:54,359
- What?
- Tamako Matsubara.

165
00:08:54,426 --> 00:08:56,328
HUH? A JAPANESE NAME?

166
00:08:56,395 --> 00:08:58,930
- That's my Japanese name.
- How do you have a Japanese name?

167
00:08:58,997 --> 00:09:00,699
I went to school for a bit

168
00:09:00,766 --> 00:09:04,002
during the Japanese occupation,
but it all ended when they lost.

169
00:09:04,069 --> 00:09:07,773
A few months into first grade,
things went haywire.

170
00:09:07,839 --> 00:09:09,474
Really?

171
00:09:09,541 --> 00:09:12,310
- So after you started school?
- After I started.

172
00:09:12,811 --> 00:09:15,547
It must've been around summer
because I began in spring.

173
00:09:15,614 --> 00:09:17,582
So I went to school for a bit
and studied Japanese there.

174
00:09:17,649 --> 00:09:20,218
Then things went haywire for Japan.

175
00:09:20,285 --> 00:09:23,255
We threw out the Japanese
who lived in Korea

176
00:09:23,321 --> 00:09:25,223
and Koreans in Japan were sent back.

177
00:09:25,290 --> 00:09:26,691
They exchanged places.

178
00:09:26,758 --> 00:09:28,493
How old were you back then?

179
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:29,895
I was probably

180
00:09:30,529 --> 00:09:33,999
eight or nine, because we didn't
start school early back then.

181
00:09:34,066 --> 00:09:35,734
I must've been nine. I don't know.

182
00:09:36,268 --> 00:09:38,703
That was what happened.
I studied for a couple of months.

183
00:09:38,770 --> 00:09:40,205
I stopped
after learning just a little.

184
00:09:40,272 --> 00:09:41,506
SHE DIDN'T STOP EVEN AFTER MANY YEARS

185
00:09:41,573 --> 00:09:43,909
Let's study English today.

186
00:09:44,476 --> 00:09:47,079
I need to know
how to write my name in English.

187
00:09:47,145 --> 00:09:48,680
"Ra Ok-ja." Wait.

188
00:09:48,747 --> 00:09:51,950
Should I write her surname
as Ra or La?

189
00:09:52,017 --> 00:09:53,385
It's the R or L sound.

190
00:09:53,452 --> 00:09:55,454
- Isn't it Ra?
- Ra is better, right?

191
00:09:55,754 --> 00:09:59,057
Look up the romanization conversion.
There's a standardized version.

192
00:10:00,158 --> 00:10:03,662
HE FOUND THE ROMANIZATION
OF HER NAME, THANKS TO BOSS PARK

193
00:10:04,196 --> 00:10:05,197
It's Ra.

194
00:10:05,831 --> 00:10:08,867
Now, this is
how you write your English name.

195
00:10:08,934 --> 00:10:09,935
Write it down here.

196
00:10:10,368 --> 00:10:12,170
I'll write it down for you,
so try to read it.

197
00:10:12,237 --> 00:10:13,405
I'll do that.

198
00:10:14,039 --> 00:10:15,373
You have to write it down for me.

199
00:10:18,176 --> 00:10:20,912
You have to write it down first
to know that it's my name.

200
00:10:21,513 --> 00:10:22,914
Look at this.

201
00:10:22,981 --> 00:10:25,951
Let's say a foreigner
came here to Muju.

202
00:10:26,017 --> 00:10:29,654
Then you'll greet them in English.

203
00:10:31,289 --> 00:10:32,290
Repeat after me.

204
00:10:32,924 --> 00:10:34,593
WITH THE HAND

205
00:10:34,659 --> 00:10:35,760
- Is that "Hello"?
- Yes.

206
00:10:35,827 --> 00:10:36,828
That's how you say hello.

207
00:10:37,596 --> 00:10:39,397
- Something "Hey, there"?
- That's "Hey, there."

208
00:10:39,464 --> 00:10:42,033
- It's "Hi."
- "Hi."

209
00:10:42,100 --> 00:10:43,568
- That's how you say hello.
- Hi.

210
00:10:43,635 --> 00:10:48,340
- "I am Ra Ok-ja."
- "Hi, I am Ra Ok-ja."

211
00:10:52,711 --> 00:10:55,413
- That's it. You have to memorize it.
- Okay.

212
00:10:55,480 --> 00:10:57,315
Next, what does this say?

213
00:10:57,816 --> 00:11:00,018
This? "Thank you."

214
00:11:00,085 --> 00:11:01,386
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

215
00:11:01,453 --> 00:11:03,021
- How about this?
- "Thank you."

216
00:11:03,088 --> 00:11:04,122
How do you read this?

217
00:11:05,257 --> 00:11:07,292
THANK YOU!

218
00:11:07,359 --> 00:11:10,562
THANK YOU!

219
00:11:10,629 --> 00:11:12,831
You speak English so well
that you can go to America now.

220
00:11:13,198 --> 00:11:15,066
- Go where?
- America. You can go there now.

221
00:11:15,133 --> 00:11:17,035
Go where? I can't go anywhere.

222
00:11:17,102 --> 00:11:19,171
THE CHEEKIEST GUY AROUND HERE

223
00:11:19,638 --> 00:11:21,406
WHAT A CUTE CONVERSATION

224
00:11:22,207 --> 00:11:23,341
All right.

225
00:11:23,408 --> 00:11:26,111
Come and visit
when you have time in the summer.

226
00:11:26,178 --> 00:11:27,379
Of course, I should come.

227
00:11:27,445 --> 00:11:30,081
Come by when I have
more goods at my place.

228
00:11:30,148 --> 00:11:32,517
- I have to return for peaches.
- Well, that too.

229
00:11:32,584 --> 00:11:34,419
I don't grow them,
but you can have them here.

230
00:11:34,486 --> 00:11:38,156
But I'll cook for you at my place,
so you can come and eat there.

231
00:11:39,024 --> 00:11:40,225
Sure.

232
00:11:40,992 --> 00:11:42,627
SMILE

233
00:11:43,161 --> 00:11:45,530
Let's go over there
and try the English you learned.

234
00:11:45,597 --> 00:11:47,299
Say, "Hi, I am Ra Ok-ja."

235
00:11:47,365 --> 00:11:48,934
EXCITED TO MAKE USE OF IT

236
00:11:49,000 --> 00:11:50,569
- Is your lesson over?
- Yes.

237
00:11:52,237 --> 00:11:53,638
- Is your lesson over?
- Yes.

238
00:11:53,705 --> 00:11:55,974
SHE SUDDENLY SHOUTS, "HI!"

239
00:11:56,041 --> 00:11:57,309
WHISPERING

240
00:11:57,375 --> 00:11:59,945
I AM RA OK-JA

241
00:12:00,712 --> 00:12:03,515
THANK YOU!

242
00:12:03,582 --> 00:12:06,785
- I had him write my name in English.
- That's awesome.

243
00:12:06,851 --> 00:12:08,720
- You're the best.
- Teach me more.

244
00:12:08,787 --> 00:12:09,921
I can do a few more.

245
00:12:10,021 --> 00:12:11,022
THE TEACHER'S PROUD

246
00:12:11,089 --> 00:12:13,091
- Bye, Ms. Ra.
- Goodbye.

247
00:12:13,158 --> 00:12:15,026
- Thanks.
- What will you do at home?

248
00:12:15,093 --> 00:12:16,394
Bye.

249
00:12:17,662 --> 00:12:20,332
- Recap our lesson as you watch TV.
- Of course.

250
00:12:20,398 --> 00:12:22,567
- I'll practice.
- You have to review and practice.

251
00:12:22,634 --> 00:12:25,237
- It's fun to learn to read or write.
- I know.

252
00:12:25,303 --> 00:12:26,805
- It's a lot of fun.
- It's fun to study, too.

253
00:12:26,871 --> 00:12:29,808
- It's a bit slippery here. Careful.
- I'm fine. It's not that slippery.

254
00:12:29,874 --> 00:12:31,776
It's a lot of fun to study.

255
00:12:31,843 --> 00:12:34,346
- Make sure you eat when you go home.
- I always eat my meals.

256
00:12:34,412 --> 00:12:36,715
- Call me if anything happens.
- Of course.

257
00:12:36,781 --> 00:12:38,350
- Okay.
- Okay. Bye.

258
00:12:38,617 --> 00:12:40,652
THANK YOU

259
00:12:40,719 --> 00:12:41,720
Bye.

260
00:12:41,786 --> 00:12:43,989
THANK YOU!

261
00:12:44,889 --> 00:12:47,092
SHE MAKES USE OF IT ALREADY

262
00:12:47,359 --> 00:12:49,261
PLEASED

263
00:12:50,328 --> 00:12:52,163
THANK YOU

264
00:12:54,165 --> 00:12:56,134
THANK YOU!

265
00:12:57,235 --> 00:12:58,603
THANK YOU!

266
00:12:58,670 --> 00:13:00,739
Thank you and hello.

267
00:13:00,805 --> 00:13:04,042
THANK YOU, SANG-YI,
FOR THE NEW PHRASE!

268
00:13:05,210 --> 00:13:07,279
Ms. Ra is so witty.

269
00:13:07,846 --> 00:13:09,514
- Why do you say so?
- As she was leaving

270
00:13:09,581 --> 00:13:13,285
she turned around and said,
"Thank you!" in English.

271
00:13:16,888 --> 00:13:19,924
THE LESSON IS OVER,
BUT HE'S STILL STYLING HIS HAIR

272
00:13:20,625 --> 00:13:23,194
You asked me to keep your hair down,
but I'm pulling it back.

273
00:13:24,029 --> 00:13:27,032
It keeps going further back,
including my sideburns and bangs.

274
00:13:30,068 --> 00:13:33,338
IT NEEDS SOMETHING MORE

275
00:13:34,739 --> 00:13:37,676
BOSS PARK ADDS A STRAND OF HIS TASTE

276
00:13:38,710 --> 00:13:39,978
Does this make you look too cheeky?

277
00:13:40,879 --> 00:13:42,914
AN UNEXPECTED CHEEKY STYLE

278
00:13:43,748 --> 00:13:45,383
LAUGHING ON MUTE
AS HE TEASES DONG-YEON

279
00:13:45,450 --> 00:13:46,518
Wait.

280
00:13:46,584 --> 00:13:48,219
- The cool cook.
- I look like Tomato Doppi.

281
00:13:48,286 --> 00:13:50,488
Tomato Doppi

282
00:13:53,692 --> 00:13:56,661
You do this look for award shows.
This single strand in the middle.

283
00:13:56,728 --> 00:13:57,929
BOSS PARK DOING WHATEVER HE WANTS TO

284
00:13:57,996 --> 00:13:59,264
No, I do it from time to time.

285
00:14:01,333 --> 00:14:04,002
HE CAN'T HELP BUT SMILE

286
00:14:04,069 --> 00:14:05,470
Why do you keep smiling
as you do my hair?

287
00:14:06,404 --> 00:14:08,406
So? Does he look cool?

288
00:14:08,907 --> 00:14:10,208
You look great with your hair back.

289
00:14:10,275 --> 00:14:11,376
- Right?
- Yes, I mean it.

290
00:14:11,443 --> 00:14:13,178
WALKING AWAY

291
00:14:14,012 --> 00:14:15,747
What about this single strand?

292
00:14:16,781 --> 00:14:18,950
SANG-YI?

293
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:23,421
He wasn't that far
that he couldn't hear me.

294
00:14:24,756 --> 00:14:27,125
HE WAS GETTING READY TO OPEN
AND REALLY DIDN'T HEAR HIM

295
00:14:27,692 --> 00:14:30,395
DO I REALLY LOOK COOL?

296
00:14:31,696 --> 00:14:34,866
FOCUSING BACK
ON STYLING DONG-YEON'S HAIR

297
00:14:36,468 --> 00:14:38,737
HIS HAIR CONTINUES TO SLICK BACK

298
00:14:41,439 --> 00:14:43,007
How much of my hair
are you slicking back?

299
00:14:46,478 --> 00:14:48,413
LAUGHING

300
00:14:50,248 --> 00:14:51,583
What's up?

301
00:14:51,649 --> 00:14:54,085
- What's going on?
- First, he asked what hair I wanted

302
00:14:54,152 --> 00:14:56,721
so I told him to part my hair
and let it flow down.

303
00:14:56,788 --> 00:14:58,123
But he began to slick it back...

304
00:14:58,189 --> 00:14:59,190
HE GETS PLAYFUL AROUND DONG-YEON

305
00:14:59,257 --> 00:15:01,226
...and put everything back just now.

306
00:15:01,292 --> 00:15:04,195
He pulled my whole hair back.
Does he want to put it all back?

307
00:15:05,263 --> 00:15:06,264
Boss PARK...

308
00:15:08,099 --> 00:15:10,268
is a warm-hearted man, right?

309
00:15:10,335 --> 00:15:14,773
He's someone who listens to everyone
and makes sure everyone is heard.

310
00:15:16,474 --> 00:15:17,475
However

311
00:15:17,542 --> 00:15:20,178
he didn't care much
for my opinion as a customer.

312
00:15:21,679 --> 00:15:23,281
Or did he not hear me?

313
00:15:24,816 --> 00:15:26,618
That's what I thought.

314
00:15:26,684 --> 00:15:28,586
PRESSING HIS LIPS

315
00:15:28,653 --> 00:15:31,389
He pulled my whole hair back.
Does he want to put it all back?

316
00:15:32,357 --> 00:15:34,426
- How far are you taking this?
- It's up to the hairdresser.

317
00:15:34,492 --> 00:15:36,861
- Yes, it's up to the boss.
- My gosh.

318
00:15:36,928 --> 00:15:39,531
I love where the hair is parting.

319
00:15:40,765 --> 00:15:43,735
The boss is obsessing over this.

320
00:15:45,370 --> 00:15:48,907
THE YOUNGEST GUY PRIVILEGE
LOVING TOUCHES FROM HIS COLLEAGUES

321
00:15:48,973 --> 00:15:50,141
Going this way?

322
00:15:53,745 --> 00:15:56,381
GRABS

323
00:15:58,650 --> 00:16:00,785
THE MISCHIEVOUS FACE
HE ONLY MAKES WITH DONG-YEON

324
00:16:00,852 --> 00:16:01,986
Careful.

325
00:16:02,987 --> 00:16:04,789
You know the scalp thing, right?

326
00:16:04,856 --> 00:16:06,291
- Wait.
- I have to do this.

327
00:16:06,357 --> 00:16:07,492
Don't you know?

328
00:16:07,559 --> 00:16:08,827
Grabbing my hair like this?

329
00:16:09,427 --> 00:16:11,663
What do you mean? I didn't do that.

330
00:16:12,697 --> 00:16:15,600
FINALLY FREED FROM THE CUTTING CAPE

331
00:16:15,967 --> 00:16:17,735
What do you think? Not bad, right?

332
00:16:18,403 --> 00:16:19,404
No.

333
00:16:19,471 --> 00:16:20,939
Hey, you honestly look great.

334
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:25,543
BOSS PARK DOESN'T FINISH
UNTIL THE FINAL TOUCH

335
00:16:26,277 --> 00:16:29,080
You look great, Dong-yeon.
You're looking better and better.

336
00:16:29,881 --> 00:16:33,251
MAYBE I DO LOOK GOOD

337
00:16:34,152 --> 00:16:35,620
HIS HAIR MATCHES HIS STYLE
WITHOUT THE CAPE

338
00:16:35,687 --> 00:16:36,855
- Let me know if it's hot.
- Okay.

339
00:16:43,695 --> 00:16:45,263
CHECKING THE TIME

340
00:16:46,564 --> 00:16:48,800
- It took two hours.
- It took two hours?

341
00:16:50,301 --> 00:16:52,003
- That's a new record.
- Let's go.

342
00:16:52,837 --> 00:16:54,873
Thank you. Good work.

343
00:16:55,640 --> 00:16:59,577
BOSS PARK'S HAIRSTYLE
CRAFTED WITH LOVE

344
00:16:59,844 --> 00:17:00,845
Look at me.

345
00:17:01,880 --> 00:17:03,181
GIGGLES

346
00:17:03,681 --> 00:17:05,083
I don't know if I did a good job.

347
00:17:07,619 --> 00:17:11,322
HALF-RELIEVED, HALF-WORRIED

348
00:17:11,756 --> 00:17:14,592
DONG-YEON SEEMS TO LOVE THE NEW HAIR
UNLIKE EARLIER

349
00:17:14,659 --> 00:17:15,760
I wonder if he's okay

350
00:17:16,561 --> 00:17:17,595
with his hair.

351
00:17:17,662 --> 00:17:21,466
BOSS PARK IS WORRIED
ABOUT THE FIRST CUT HE GAVE HIM

352
00:17:22,166 --> 00:17:26,838
GOSH, I HOPE IT WENT WELL

353
00:17:28,306 --> 00:17:29,440
- Oh, my.
- Hello.

354
00:17:30,174 --> 00:17:32,210
You honestly look really cool.

355
00:17:33,211 --> 00:17:34,212
DO I?

356
00:17:34,279 --> 00:17:37,515
PUTTING ON AN ACCESSORY
AS SOON AS HE GETS A COMPLIMENT

357
00:17:39,250 --> 00:17:43,121
Q. DO YOU LIKE BOSS PARK'S HAIRCUT?

358
00:17:43,187 --> 00:17:45,857
DYING TO SPEAK

359
00:17:47,792 --> 00:17:50,995
BOSS PARK IS CLEANING UP
WITHOUT A CLUE

360
00:17:51,896 --> 00:17:53,498
It took about two hours.

361
00:17:56,167 --> 00:17:58,036
To be honest

362
00:17:58,102 --> 00:18:01,272
I did not want
to slick all of my hair back.

363
00:18:02,140 --> 00:18:03,141
However

364
00:18:03,575 --> 00:18:06,144
I told him
he could do whatever he wanted to.

365
00:18:07,011 --> 00:18:08,212
HEY, DONG-YEON

366
00:18:08,279 --> 00:18:09,480
I CAN

367
00:18:09,547 --> 00:18:10,815
HEAR YOU RIGHT NOW

368
00:18:11,749 --> 00:18:14,118
CHUCKLES

369
00:18:14,652 --> 00:18:16,654
I'm satisfied.
No, I'm pleased with it.

370
00:18:18,790 --> 00:18:20,391
Yes, thank you.

371
00:18:20,458 --> 00:18:22,160
EMPLOYEE REVIEW

372
00:18:22,226 --> 00:18:25,697
IT TOOK TOO LONG,
BUT THE BOSS IS GOOD-LOOKING

373
00:18:30,201 --> 00:18:32,937
SANG-YI STARES OUT THE WINDOW

374
00:18:33,004 --> 00:18:36,541
WITH A SERIOUS LOOK ON HIS FACE

375
00:18:37,208 --> 00:18:41,145
IS HE WAITING FOR A CUSTOMER?

376
00:18:42,513 --> 00:18:45,783
THEN HE BRINGS OUT
A BOX FULL OF THINGS

377
00:18:46,918 --> 00:18:50,855
FULL OF ART SUPPLIES,
SUCH AS PAINT AND ROLLERS

378
00:18:52,357 --> 00:18:53,691
THE PLACE HE ARRIVED

379
00:18:53,758 --> 00:18:55,994
LOOKING RATHER DETERMINED

380
00:18:56,628 --> 00:19:01,766
WHY IS HE STANDING
IN FRONT OF A WHITE WALL?

381
00:19:02,133 --> 00:19:04,435
We were wondering
what we could leave behind

382
00:19:05,103 --> 00:19:09,207
so people could remember us
and look back on our time together.

383
00:19:10,842 --> 00:19:12,276
Here's my opinion.

384
00:19:13,144 --> 00:19:15,480
Do you see
that clean wall out in front?

385
00:19:15,747 --> 00:19:17,515
Doesn't it look too empty?

386
00:19:17,582 --> 00:19:18,850
- Out there?
- Yes.

387
00:19:18,916 --> 00:19:22,320
They can draw something there,
but I'm not sure if they can do that.

388
00:19:22,387 --> 00:19:24,222
AN IDEA THEY GOT
FROM THE VILLAGE CHIEF

389
00:19:24,288 --> 00:19:29,494
We decided to leave a mural in Muju
that reflects how we feel.

390
00:19:30,728 --> 00:19:32,830
Let's come up
with an idea by ourselves.

391
00:19:32,897 --> 00:19:34,165
What should we paint?

392
00:19:34,899 --> 00:19:39,570
WONDERING WHAT THEY'LL PAINT
TO MAKE IT MORE MEANINGFUL

393
00:19:40,304 --> 00:19:41,873
A REALIZATION

394
00:19:42,707 --> 00:19:44,709
HE MUST'VE THOUGHT
OF A GOOD IDEA

395
00:19:45,476 --> 00:19:46,711
- Listen up.
- Yes.

396
00:19:48,046 --> 00:19:49,447
CURIOUS

397
00:19:49,514 --> 00:19:50,948
We'll put up a mirror.

398
00:19:51,015 --> 00:19:52,717
Then people can come
and take pictures.

399
00:19:53,084 --> 00:19:55,353
That's a great idea
to let people come and take pictures.

400
00:19:55,420 --> 00:19:56,921
- Because if you think about it,
- Right.

401
00:19:56,988 --> 00:19:58,489
pictures are all that's left
of your memories.

402
00:19:59,657 --> 00:20:01,993
THINKING

403
00:20:02,660 --> 00:20:04,829
DRAWING

404
00:20:05,029 --> 00:20:07,932
HE BEGINS TO SKETCH THEIR MURAL!

405
00:20:09,667 --> 00:20:13,171
WHAT WILL BO GUM COME UP WITH?

406
00:20:13,237 --> 00:20:15,039
Do you understand
what I'm trying to get at?

407
00:20:15,673 --> 00:20:17,308
I'm really bad at drawing.

408
00:20:18,576 --> 00:20:21,612
- This is a peach tree with flowers.
- The peach blossom tree.

409
00:20:22,346 --> 00:20:26,718
SYMBOL OF MUJU VILLAGE
PEACH BLOSSOMS

410
00:20:27,819 --> 00:20:29,053
Peaches.

411
00:20:29,420 --> 00:20:30,988
So it looks like this.

412
00:20:31,355 --> 00:20:33,925
Let's ask people to draw
flowers and peaches together.

413
00:20:33,991 --> 00:20:35,426
- It'll be a collaboration.
- Yes.

414
00:20:35,493 --> 00:20:36,994
WILL IT TURN OUT
JUST LIKE BO GUM'S SKETCH?

415
00:20:37,462 --> 00:20:39,497
I thought it would be nice

416
00:20:39,564 --> 00:20:42,233
if we could leave traces
and memories of us behind.

417
00:20:42,500 --> 00:20:46,370
I thought it'd be more significant
if we painted it together.

418
00:20:46,437 --> 00:20:48,139
MORE MEANINGFUL
WITH THE VILLAGERS' PARTICIPATION

419
00:20:48,206 --> 00:20:51,476
Ms. Ra, you're an artist!

420
00:20:51,542 --> 00:20:53,745
You can draw however you want to.

421
00:20:53,811 --> 00:20:56,013
EVERYONE PARTICIPATED
IN MAKING THIS MURAL

422
00:20:56,080 --> 00:20:58,583
That's all right, ma'am.
That's what we call art.

423
00:21:00,384 --> 00:21:01,385
It's art.

424
00:21:01,886 --> 00:21:03,521
It's okay to make a mistake.

425
00:21:03,588 --> 00:21:06,424
- I can always start over.
- Yes, you can start over.

426
00:21:06,491 --> 00:21:08,126
My gosh. That was so touching.

427
00:21:08,192 --> 00:21:10,461
HOW WILL THE MURAL TURN OUT
WITH EVERYONE'S PARTICIPATION?

428
00:21:10,528 --> 00:21:11,729
I'm so touched.

429
00:21:11,796 --> 00:21:15,032
A collaboration by Apseom Village
and The Village Barber.

430
00:21:17,135 --> 00:21:20,138
Before we start,
let me give you some chalk.

431
00:21:21,005 --> 00:21:23,407
- Let's each sketch in our own style.
- Okay.

432
00:21:24,108 --> 00:21:27,812
First, we'll start
with the mirror in the middle.

433
00:21:28,846 --> 00:21:31,082
My father ran
a paint store for a long time.

434
00:21:31,149 --> 00:21:33,317
DURING HIS PRACTICE
FOR THE NAIL TECHNICIAN LICENSE

435
00:21:33,384 --> 00:21:34,552
It's chalk, so it doesn't matter.

436
00:21:34,619 --> 00:21:37,789
We have to paint
over the sketch anyway.

437
00:21:38,723 --> 00:21:39,891
Let's just go at it.

438
00:21:40,291 --> 00:21:43,594
HE BEGINS TO SKETCH
A TREE WITH PEACH BLOSSOMS

439
00:21:44,662 --> 00:21:47,665
I did my best
with what I learned back in school

440
00:21:47,732 --> 00:21:50,067
during stage production classes.

441
00:21:51,602 --> 00:21:56,174
POSING LIKE A PRO

442
00:21:57,675 --> 00:22:01,612
HE HAD ONLY DRAWN
ON TINY NAILS UNTIL THIS DAY

443
00:22:01,679 --> 00:22:03,281
Like it's in full bloom.

444
00:22:03,347 --> 00:22:06,384
SANG-YI FINALLY SPREADS HIS WINGS
ON A HUGE WALL

445
00:22:06,450 --> 00:22:08,152
I see. Just like that?

446
00:22:09,987 --> 00:22:11,455
DONG-YEON DRAWS A TREE WITH PEACHES

447
00:22:11,522 --> 00:22:12,757
A peach blossom tree.

448
00:22:14,659 --> 00:22:18,596
DRAWS THE SKETCH IN ONE STROKE

449
00:22:18,663 --> 00:22:19,931
LET'S SEE

450
00:22:19,997 --> 00:22:21,866
It looks like a monster's hand.

451
00:22:21,933 --> 00:22:23,634
CHUCKLES

452
00:22:23,701 --> 00:22:26,971
SPOOKY

453
00:22:27,538 --> 00:22:28,840
Who drew that red tree?

454
00:22:28,906 --> 00:22:30,174
- Me.
- It looks great.

455
00:22:30,241 --> 00:22:31,442
- That?
- Yes.

456
00:22:32,310 --> 00:22:34,312
That was a funny tone. "That?"

457
00:22:35,213 --> 00:22:39,417
Let's ask every customer
to draw a peach here.

458
00:22:40,251 --> 00:22:41,652
ACTING IT OUT

459
00:22:41,719 --> 00:22:45,022
- Say, "Please draw a peach."
- Okay.

460
00:22:45,790 --> 00:22:47,225
Can you see the yellow? No?

461
00:22:47,291 --> 00:22:48,392
- I can see it.
- Can you?

462
00:22:48,459 --> 00:22:49,460
THE SKETCH IS DONE
THE MIRROR'S SPOT

463
00:22:49,527 --> 00:22:50,862
I can see it clearly.

464
00:22:50,928 --> 00:22:52,864
Does this sketch of a tree look okay?

465
00:22:52,930 --> 00:22:54,732
- Yes, it looks fine.
- It's so good.

466
00:22:55,266 --> 00:22:56,334
It's not bad.

467
00:22:57,602 --> 00:22:59,637
He studied the world of art
comprehensively.

468
00:23:00,104 --> 00:23:01,606
THE SON OF A PAINT STORE OWNER

469
00:23:01,672 --> 00:23:03,941
AND A LEGENDARY FIGURE
AT KOREAN NATIONAL UNIV. OF ARTS

470
00:23:04,008 --> 00:23:05,243
I think we can

471
00:23:05,309 --> 00:23:06,777
- start painting right now.
- With brown.

472
00:23:07,612 --> 00:23:09,046
We can use

473
00:23:09,113 --> 00:23:10,915
different shades of brown
to paint the tree anyway.

474
00:23:10,982 --> 00:23:13,718
Instead of one color, it's better
to use different shades of brown.

475
00:23:13,784 --> 00:23:15,553
Do we have gesso here?

476
00:23:15,620 --> 00:23:16,854
Let's just do it.

477
00:23:16,921 --> 00:23:18,389
That's white.

478
00:23:18,456 --> 00:23:20,391
We can make mistakes.
There's white paint.

479
00:23:21,425 --> 00:23:22,593
We can make mistakes.

480
00:23:22,660 --> 00:23:23,828
Let's put tape on it first.

481
00:23:24,095 --> 00:23:26,864
SOMEONE IS APPROACHING

482
00:23:27,598 --> 00:23:30,835
IS THAT THEIR FIRST CUSTOMER?

483
00:23:31,302 --> 00:23:33,371
- We can make mistakes.
- Hello.

484
00:23:34,505 --> 00:23:36,474
- We can make mistakes.
- Hello.

485
00:23:37,742 --> 00:23:40,011
- Hello.
- Hey.

486
00:23:41,746 --> 00:23:42,880
Hey!

487
00:23:43,514 --> 00:23:44,882
Hello.

488
00:23:45,483 --> 00:23:46,984
- Hey.
- Hey!

489
00:23:47,051 --> 00:23:48,352
WHO'S THE MYSTERIOUS WOMAN
WHO SHOCKED THE TRIO?

490
00:23:52,957 --> 00:23:57,028
WALKING WITH CONFIDENCE
INTO THE VILLAGE

491
00:24:00,932 --> 00:24:05,369
TODAY'S PART-TIMER
ACTRESS KIM SO-HYUN

492
00:24:05,770 --> 00:24:07,805
PEEKING

493
00:24:08,472 --> 00:24:11,108
SNEAKY

494
00:24:12,109 --> 00:24:13,144
SO-HYUN

495
00:24:13,210 --> 00:24:14,912
Does this sketch of a tree look okay?

496
00:24:14,979 --> 00:24:16,447
- Yes, it looks fine.
- It's so good.

497
00:24:16,514 --> 00:24:19,050
THEY'RE FOCUSED ON THE MURAL,
NOT REALIZING THE PART-TIMER IS HERE

498
00:24:19,116 --> 00:24:20,851
Black. No, not black. Brown.

499
00:24:21,852 --> 00:24:23,120
Let's put tape on it first.

500
00:24:23,287 --> 00:24:24,288
NOT KNOWING SHE'S RIGHT BEHIND THEM

501
00:24:24,355 --> 00:24:25,523
Let's just do it.

502
00:24:25,589 --> 00:24:26,824
That's white.

503
00:24:27,992 --> 00:24:29,593
- We can make mistakes.
- Hello.

504
00:24:30,828 --> 00:24:32,063
- Hello.
- Hey!

505
00:24:32,129 --> 00:24:33,931
- My gosh. Hey!
- Hello.

506
00:24:38,703 --> 00:24:39,704
Hey!

507
00:24:40,471 --> 00:24:42,206
- We can make mistakes.
- Hello.

508
00:24:43,474 --> 00:24:44,508
- Hey!
- Hello.

509
00:24:44,575 --> 00:24:46,077
WIDE-EYED

510
00:24:46,143 --> 00:24:47,545
- Hey!
- Hello.

511
00:24:47,611 --> 00:24:50,414
THEIR FORMER CO-STAR
SO-HYUN IS HERE

512
00:24:51,315 --> 00:24:52,616
- So-hyun!
- So-hyun!

513
00:24:52,683 --> 00:24:54,151
- Kim Sobari.
- So-hyun!

514
00:24:54,218 --> 00:24:55,486
- So-hyun!
- So-hyun!

515
00:24:55,553 --> 00:24:56,988
- Kim Sobari.
- So-hyun!

516
00:24:57,054 --> 00:24:59,390
- Hey, look at your hair!
- Are you serious?

517
00:24:59,457 --> 00:25:00,591
Why is your hair so long?

518
00:25:00,658 --> 00:25:01,859
- It grew out a lot.
- You look good.

519
00:25:01,926 --> 00:25:03,294
- It's long, isn't it?
- Hey.

520
00:25:03,361 --> 00:25:05,296
PEOPLE IN THIS LINE OF WORK
NOTICE THE HAIR FIRST

521
00:25:05,363 --> 00:25:06,497
- Hey.
- First of all...

522
00:25:06,564 --> 00:25:09,266
- First of all...
- It's so good to see you!

523
00:25:09,333 --> 00:25:10,868
- Let's go.
- Let's go inside.

524
00:25:10,935 --> 00:25:12,937
I was so surprised
to see everyone out here.

525
00:25:13,004 --> 00:25:15,740
- Hey, you. Wait.
- My gosh.

526
00:25:16,807 --> 00:25:18,242
- I got chills.
- It's so good to see you.

527
00:25:18,309 --> 00:25:19,744
This place is so cute.

528
00:25:19,810 --> 00:25:21,812
- Really? Welcome.
- The sign is so cute.

529
00:25:21,879 --> 00:25:24,015
- Let's go inside. It's cold.
- Come on in.

530
00:25:24,081 --> 00:25:25,983
Aren't you busy
with your new drama production?

531
00:25:26,050 --> 00:25:27,918
We're shooting right now.

532
00:25:28,352 --> 00:25:30,087
- I'm glad you're here.
- Yes, we're so glad.

533
00:25:30,154 --> 00:25:31,522
Welcome.

534
00:25:32,323 --> 00:25:33,457
So-hyun.

535
00:25:34,692 --> 00:25:35,826
Put it on.

536
00:25:37,561 --> 00:25:39,296
FIRST, GET READY TO WORK

537
00:25:39,530 --> 00:25:40,831
Let me do this for you.

538
00:25:41,265 --> 00:25:43,134
You have to cross these
before you put it on.

539
00:25:43,868 --> 00:25:45,036
- How cute.
- I didn't expect you.

540
00:25:45,102 --> 00:25:47,538
- She really came.
- Wait. Hold this. Put your head in.

541
00:25:47,605 --> 00:25:50,841
- Hold it right there.
- I didn't think you'd expect me.

542
00:25:50,908 --> 00:25:53,577
You recently co-starred
with those two

543
00:25:54,345 --> 00:25:56,847
- and we're acquainted, too.
- We are.

544
00:25:56,914 --> 00:25:58,115
It's been forever since we met.

545
00:25:58,182 --> 00:26:00,451
- It's been forever.
- Did you two work together?

546
00:26:01,052 --> 00:26:03,587
So-hyun has an actor friend
who's very close to her

547
00:26:03,654 --> 00:26:05,222
who's friends with me too.

548
00:26:05,723 --> 00:26:07,525
So, you're all friends.

549
00:26:07,591 --> 00:26:08,959
- My gosh.
- Hey.

550
00:26:09,026 --> 00:26:11,228
- Thank you for coming.
- It's good to see you.

551
00:26:11,295 --> 00:26:12,596
- It's nice to be here.
- Welcome.

552
00:26:12,663 --> 00:26:14,965
This is so weird.
I feel like I'm in a dream.

553
00:26:15,032 --> 00:26:16,467
It's kind of weird.

554
00:26:16,801 --> 00:26:20,037
- You look great, So-hyun.
- Thanks.

555
00:26:20,104 --> 00:26:21,772
- I love that new style on you.
- You do?

556
00:26:21,839 --> 00:26:24,141
Yes, I've never seen
your hair like this.

557
00:26:24,208 --> 00:26:25,576
- I've never done this.
- Right?

558
00:26:25,643 --> 00:26:26,644
Never like this.

559
00:26:26,710 --> 00:26:28,679
You look different
from your character, Han-na.

560
00:26:28,746 --> 00:26:30,514
Yes, she's a different character.

561
00:26:30,581 --> 00:26:32,083
So this is the new character.

562
00:26:32,650 --> 00:26:35,786
- It's so pretty. I mean it.
- That haircut looks great on you.

563
00:26:35,853 --> 00:26:37,555
The haircut?

564
00:26:38,856 --> 00:26:41,358
- Should I have done it here?
- Yes, we do everything.

565
00:26:41,425 --> 00:26:42,526
We do everything.

566
00:26:43,360 --> 00:26:45,129
He and I met recently, right?

567
00:26:45,196 --> 00:26:46,864
- We met up a few times.
- Yes, back then.

568
00:26:46,931 --> 00:26:48,332
But I didn't say anything.

569
00:26:48,399 --> 00:26:49,700
- I already knew then.
- Not at all.

570
00:26:49,767 --> 00:26:52,570
- You already knew?
- Yes.

571
00:26:52,636 --> 00:26:53,871
You're so cheeky.

572
00:26:53,938 --> 00:26:55,639
You're as sly as a snake.

573
00:26:55,706 --> 00:26:57,374
- I knew.
- Back then? Already?

574
00:26:57,441 --> 00:26:58,909
But I wanted to come in secret,
so I asked

575
00:26:58,976 --> 00:27:01,278
"So what are you going to do there?"

576
00:27:01,712 --> 00:27:04,014
I even asked,
"What can you do there?"

577
00:27:04,615 --> 00:27:05,950
I told her everything.

578
00:27:06,383 --> 00:27:09,453
Yes, he told me everything
about doing the nails and whatnot.

579
00:27:09,520 --> 00:27:10,955
I was like, "I see."

580
00:27:11,021 --> 00:27:12,623
Has it been a while
since you three have met?

581
00:27:12,690 --> 00:27:14,358
- Very much.
- Totally.

582
00:27:15,126 --> 00:27:16,727
YOU GOT SOMETHING ON YOUR FACE

583
00:27:16,794 --> 00:27:18,562
- Do you need a mirror?
- Yes.

584
00:27:19,530 --> 00:27:21,265
Here it is.

585
00:27:21,332 --> 00:27:22,466
NICE TO THE FIRST FEMALE PART-TIMER

586
00:27:22,533 --> 00:27:24,869
- I always have it ready.
- Okay.

587
00:27:24,935 --> 00:27:27,905
- Is there anything I can do to help?
- Not at all.

588
00:27:30,174 --> 00:27:31,842
Man, I forgot to bring my weapon.

589
00:27:32,576 --> 00:27:34,845
- Your knife? I'll run back home.
- No, I can use this.

590
00:27:34,912 --> 00:27:36,780
- I'll go.
- No, it's okay. Don't do that.

591
00:27:36,847 --> 00:27:38,916
I said I'd ask twice,
so I'll stop asking.

592
00:27:39,550 --> 00:27:40,618
Right!

593
00:27:41,085 --> 00:27:42,853
- It's over.
- It's done.

594
00:27:43,354 --> 00:27:45,289
- He gets two chances?
- Everyone here

595
00:27:45,356 --> 00:27:46,790
is way too caring.

596
00:27:47,658 --> 00:27:49,493
- So we said we'd ask twice.
- Everyone says it's fine?

597
00:27:49,560 --> 00:27:50,628
Do you want a bite?

598
00:27:51,162 --> 00:27:52,329
No.

599
00:27:52,396 --> 00:27:54,231
- It's the last time. Want some?
- Yes!

600
00:27:54,298 --> 00:27:56,133
That's our last chance.

601
00:27:56,600 --> 00:27:57,868
- We'll only ask twice.
- Okay.

602
00:27:57,935 --> 00:28:00,204
- I'll remember that, too.
- Take a note.

603
00:28:00,271 --> 00:28:03,107
But So-hyun answers the question
even when we ask her just once.

604
00:28:03,174 --> 00:28:05,743
- Yes, I give a straight answer.
- You're the honest type.

605
00:28:06,510 --> 00:28:07,678
Unlike you two.

606
00:28:09,013 --> 00:28:12,216
THANKS TO A SISTERLY PART-TIMER,
THINGS ARE WARMING UP QUICKLY

607
00:28:12,516 --> 00:28:14,351
- We're rather slow today.
- We are.

608
00:28:14,418 --> 00:28:16,287
Are you slow right now? Really?

609
00:28:16,353 --> 00:28:18,889
- We're rather slow today.
- Is that so?

610
00:28:18,956 --> 00:28:20,157
OPEN
BUT HAD 0 CUSTOMERS

611
00:28:20,224 --> 00:28:23,160
We were usually as busy as bees.
We've had so many people here.

612
00:28:23,227 --> 00:28:25,196
I'm excited. I hope we have
lots of customers today, too.

613
00:28:25,262 --> 00:28:27,765
We'll have many customers today

614
00:28:27,831 --> 00:28:29,533
so you have to learn
how to shampoo hair

615
00:28:29,600 --> 00:28:32,937
assist in the kitchen,
clean up, and do the laundry.

616
00:28:33,003 --> 00:28:34,572
You have to learn to do everything.

617
00:28:34,638 --> 00:28:36,440
- Okay. I can do that very well.
- Are you ready?

618
00:28:36,507 --> 00:28:37,942
- Right? Okay.
- Yes.

619
00:28:42,012 --> 00:28:43,414
SHE PUTS HER JACKET BACK ON?

620
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:45,549
- I think she'll be cold like this.
- No, I'm fine.

621
00:28:46,283 --> 00:28:47,618
Now that So-hyun is here

622
00:28:47,685 --> 00:28:49,353
I want to ask her to make
fish-shaped buns.

623
00:28:49,853 --> 00:28:51,555
- We were on a roll.
- You make fish-shaped buns?

624
00:28:51,622 --> 00:28:52,923
I want to make steamed buns, too.

625
00:28:52,990 --> 00:28:55,159
- Steamed buns!
- That's your nickname! Steamed Bun!

626
00:28:55,226 --> 00:28:56,727
- You're right.
- Steamed Bun.

627
00:28:56,794 --> 00:28:58,262
You can start painting now.

628
00:28:58,329 --> 00:29:00,598
Do you want to use brown paint
to paint the trees?

629
00:29:00,664 --> 00:29:01,732
Okay.

630
00:29:02,633 --> 00:29:05,236
- I've never done this before.
- Me too.

631
00:29:05,869 --> 00:29:07,538
- Should I pour a little?
- Sure.

632
00:29:09,373 --> 00:29:10,874
That's too...

633
00:29:10,941 --> 00:29:12,576
- Isn't it too red?
- Yes, it's reddish brown.

634
00:29:12,643 --> 00:29:14,245
Should we mix it with black?

635
00:29:14,311 --> 00:29:16,347
- Yellow? A bit...
- Yellow?

636
00:29:16,413 --> 00:29:20,084
ADDING YELLOW PAINT
TO MAKE BRIGHTER BROWN!

637
00:29:20,150 --> 00:29:21,218
Will it work?

638
00:29:23,554 --> 00:29:26,724
- Do you do dyes, too?
- Yes.

639
00:29:26,790 --> 00:29:28,626
I dye the whole hair
and do highlights.

640
00:29:29,627 --> 00:29:31,862
You must know how colors mix.

641
00:29:31,929 --> 00:29:33,297
What you need
to make a certain color.

642
00:29:33,998 --> 00:29:35,299
Well, I do.

643
00:29:35,366 --> 00:29:36,900
- I learned that.
- Yes?

644
00:29:37,434 --> 00:29:40,104
But the elders here
mostly color their hair

645
00:29:40,871 --> 00:29:44,475
- just dark brown or black.
- That's true.

646
00:29:44,541 --> 00:29:46,443
I never got to dye
anyone's hair a bright color.

647
00:29:49,179 --> 00:29:52,449
COME TO THINK OF IT
HE'S RIGHT

648
00:29:55,019 --> 00:29:56,287
- Is this it?
- What?

649
00:29:57,021 --> 00:29:58,522
- I think it's here.
- This is it.

650
00:29:59,023 --> 00:30:00,324
Hello.

651
00:30:02,860 --> 00:30:04,094
Look, kids are walking by.

652
00:30:07,965 --> 00:30:12,436
A LOCAL RESIDENT WALKS BY
WITH A BABY IN HIS ARMS

653
00:30:14,405 --> 00:30:17,007
ANOTHER CHILD

654
00:30:23,080 --> 00:30:25,516
- Hi, there.
- Hi.

655
00:30:27,117 --> 00:30:28,585
- Hi.
- Hello.

656
00:30:29,620 --> 00:30:30,788
Hello.

657
00:30:30,854 --> 00:30:32,323
- Hello.
- Goodness, it's a little baby.

658
00:30:33,223 --> 00:30:34,325
- Hello.
- Where are you going?

659
00:30:34,858 --> 00:30:35,959
- Well...
- The barbershop.

660
00:30:36,026 --> 00:30:37,061
Hair.

661
00:30:37,127 --> 00:30:38,429
- You came to cut your hair?
- Yes.

662
00:30:38,862 --> 00:30:40,130
SURPRISED

663
00:30:40,197 --> 00:30:41,598
- Really?
- Yes.

664
00:30:41,932 --> 00:30:42,933
OH, MY! A CUSTOMER!

665
00:30:43,000 --> 00:30:44,435
- You came to cut your hair?
- Yes.

666
00:30:44,501 --> 00:30:45,903
- Hey, there.
- Then let's go inside.

667
00:30:45,969 --> 00:30:47,805
- Then please excuse me.
- You should go inside. Yes.

668
00:30:48,605 --> 00:30:50,240
THEY HAD NO IDEA

669
00:30:50,307 --> 00:30:52,609
THE CHAOS THESE THREE WOULD BRING

670
00:30:53,110 --> 00:30:55,412
I just want a slight trim.

671
00:30:55,946 --> 00:30:58,082
You have thick hair,
and your hair's pretty long.

672
00:30:58,148 --> 00:30:59,283
IT'S NOT EVEN EASY TO COMB

673
00:30:59,350 --> 00:31:00,984
THE OVERLY ENERGETIC SECOND BROTHER

674
00:31:01,051 --> 00:31:02,152
Let's go!

675
00:31:02,986 --> 00:31:04,888
And paint a tiny flower there.

676
00:31:04,955 --> 00:31:06,423
- Yes, one second.
- But flowers...

677
00:31:06,490 --> 00:31:08,425
- Give me a second.
- It's not dry yet.

678
00:31:08,492 --> 00:31:09,626
One second.

679
00:31:09,693 --> 00:31:10,961
One moment, please.

680
00:31:11,028 --> 00:31:12,029
Gosh, my back.

681
00:31:12,096 --> 00:31:13,097
THEY'RE THE FIRST CUSTOMERS

682
00:31:13,931 --> 00:31:17,368
AN 18-MONTH-OLD
THEIR YOUNGEST CUSTOMER SO FAR

683
00:31:17,935 --> 00:31:19,103
DROPPING THE BABY BOTTLE

684
00:31:19,169 --> 00:31:21,939
- We need the formula.
- Please wash it again.

685
00:31:22,005 --> 00:31:23,440
Stand up.

686
00:31:23,507 --> 00:31:25,175
HE REFUSES TO CUT HIS HAIR!

687
00:31:25,943 --> 00:31:27,144
I want to cry, too.

688
00:31:29,079 --> 00:31:30,347
Did that surprise you?

689
00:31:31,849 --> 00:31:33,784
We've turned
into a kindergarten today.

690
00:31:33,851 --> 00:31:35,285
Tell me about it.

691
00:31:35,352 --> 00:31:36,487
Let's go inside.

692
00:31:36,553 --> 00:31:38,956
WILL THEY MAKE IT THROUGH THE DAY?

693
00:31:39,223 --> 00:31:41,892
Do you live here in Muju?

694
00:31:41,959 --> 00:31:43,627
- I live in the back village.
- In the back?

695
00:31:43,694 --> 00:31:46,029
- Did you come from the back?
- Yes.

696
00:31:46,397 --> 00:31:48,132
- How old are you?
- I'm ten.

697
00:31:48,198 --> 00:31:50,167
And my older brother
will start middle school.

698
00:31:50,234 --> 00:31:51,668
He'll be in seventh grade.

699
00:31:51,735 --> 00:31:53,337
- In middle school?
- Yes.

700
00:31:53,404 --> 00:31:54,905
How old is the baby?

701
00:31:55,706 --> 00:31:57,875
- He's turning two.
- He's turning two?

702
00:31:57,941 --> 00:31:59,376
THE TINIEST ONE IS 18 MONTHS OLD

703
00:32:00,411 --> 00:32:02,112
- How adorable.
- Have a seat, please.

704
00:32:02,179 --> 00:32:03,180
THEY CAME WITH THEIR YOUNGEST'S STUFF

705
00:32:03,247 --> 00:32:04,748
Have a seat.

706
00:32:04,815 --> 00:32:07,818
THE ELDEST HAS THE DIAPER BAG,
AND THE SECOND HAS THE STROLLER

707
00:32:07,885 --> 00:32:10,788
- What about the hair?
- Who's here for the haircut?

708
00:32:10,854 --> 00:32:12,990
- All three of us.
- All three?

709
00:32:13,056 --> 00:32:14,625
- Yes, all three of us.
- Oh, wow.

710
00:32:14,691 --> 00:32:15,793
How cute.

711
00:32:15,859 --> 00:32:18,295
AN ORDER FOR THREE HAIRCUTS

712
00:32:18,629 --> 00:32:20,030
INCLUDING THE 18-MONTH-OLD YOUNGEST

713
00:32:20,097 --> 00:32:21,665
All right, then.

714
00:32:21,732 --> 00:32:23,100
Who wants to go first?

715
00:32:23,734 --> 00:32:24,968
Who should we begin with?

716
00:32:25,803 --> 00:32:27,604
LET'S SEE

717
00:32:27,671 --> 00:32:30,174
- Should we start with the eldest?
- He can go first.

718
00:32:30,240 --> 00:32:31,375
- The eldest first?
- Do that.

719
00:32:31,442 --> 00:32:33,510
THE ELDEST WITH THE LONGEST HAIR
IS UP FIRST

720
00:32:34,311 --> 00:32:37,448
- Can you take your jacket off?
- We'll keep your bag and jacket.

721
00:32:37,981 --> 00:32:40,451
THE YOUNGEST ONE ESCAPE

722
00:32:40,517 --> 00:32:41,985
Come here, Seo-yul.

723
00:32:42,052 --> 00:32:43,854
Come here. Where are you going?

724
00:32:44,688 --> 00:32:45,722
Hi, there.

725
00:32:45,789 --> 00:32:47,558
That's a humidifier.

726
00:32:47,624 --> 00:32:49,893
HE NATURALLY ARRIVES
AT THE RECEPTION ROOM

727
00:32:49,960 --> 00:32:51,061
One second.

728
00:32:52,429 --> 00:32:54,465
THIS PLACE LOOKS COZY

729
00:32:54,531 --> 00:32:56,266
Yes, you can go up there.

730
00:32:56,333 --> 00:32:58,268
MAKING AN EFFORT

731
00:32:58,969 --> 00:33:00,237
Take your shoes off, though.

732
00:33:01,205 --> 00:33:04,007
Let me take the shoes off for you.
Come over here, little one.

733
00:33:04,074 --> 00:33:05,375
Come here, little one.

734
00:33:05,442 --> 00:33:07,211
- Do you want something to eat?
- Goodness.

735
00:33:07,277 --> 00:33:09,646
- Do you want to eat?
- You must want to eat something.

736
00:33:09,713 --> 00:33:11,014
I just need to take your shoes off.

737
00:33:11,081 --> 00:33:12,549
PUSHING THE TABLE FAR AWAY

738
00:33:13,684 --> 00:33:14,785
You're so cute.

739
00:33:14,852 --> 00:33:16,353
He's so tiny, isn't he?

740
00:33:18,255 --> 00:33:19,490
How cute.

741
00:33:19,556 --> 00:33:22,426
CAUTIOUSLY TAKING OFF HIS SHOES,
WHICH ARE MUCH SMALLER THAN HER PALMS

742
00:33:22,993 --> 00:33:24,928
SHE TRIES TO LOOK AFTER HIM, BUT...

743
00:33:24,995 --> 00:33:25,996
So cute.

744
00:33:26,363 --> 00:33:27,631
WRIGGLING

745
00:33:27,698 --> 00:33:29,466
- Don't lie down.
- Goodness.

746
00:33:30,734 --> 00:33:32,503
It's all right. Don't cry.

747
00:33:32,569 --> 00:33:34,171
What do I have to do to soothe him?

748
00:33:34,238 --> 00:33:37,674
I think he'll be okay
after drinking some milk.

749
00:33:37,741 --> 00:33:38,842
Milk?

750
00:33:38,909 --> 00:33:40,043
WHINING

751
00:33:40,110 --> 00:33:41,311
THE YOUNGEST THROWS A FIT

752
00:33:41,378 --> 00:33:42,379
What about this?

753
00:33:42,779 --> 00:33:43,780
You should drink this for now.

754
00:33:43,847 --> 00:33:45,849
I'm trying to make his formula.

755
00:33:45,916 --> 00:33:47,384
That's his water, though.

756
00:33:48,252 --> 00:33:49,353
He's drinking it.

757
00:33:51,822 --> 00:33:53,690
He became quiet instantly.

758
00:33:54,658 --> 00:33:55,926
You're simple-minded.

759
00:33:56,226 --> 00:33:59,596
He'll probably feel something fuzzy
when he drinks cold water.

760
00:33:59,663 --> 00:34:00,898
Hey, there.

761
00:34:00,964 --> 00:34:02,966
You're going to hurt yourself.
Careful.

762
00:34:03,500 --> 00:34:05,435
- I think he wants to sit.
- Does he?

763
00:34:05,502 --> 00:34:06,737
A 18-MONTH-OLD DEMANDS CONSTANT CARE

764
00:34:07,271 --> 00:34:08,739
SUDDENLY STOPS CRYING

765
00:34:08,805 --> 00:34:09,806
WHILE HE'S TAKING A SIP CALMLY

766
00:34:09,873 --> 00:34:11,408
You drink well.

767
00:34:11,742 --> 00:34:13,010
This isn't easy.

768
00:34:13,777 --> 00:34:15,846
LIFTING THE TABLE

769
00:34:16,480 --> 00:34:19,283
SHE FOLDS EACH LEG OF THE TABLE

770
00:34:19,816 --> 00:34:22,019
AND MOVES IT AWAY

771
00:34:23,053 --> 00:34:25,188
It's a desk.

772
00:34:25,255 --> 00:34:27,424
SHE REMOVES ALL POTENTIAL HAZARDS

773
00:34:27,491 --> 00:34:29,560
TABLE CLEARED

774
00:34:30,561 --> 00:34:31,862
WHEW

775
00:34:32,963 --> 00:34:36,500
SHE MOVES EVERYTHING ELSE
INTO THE CORNER AS WELL

776
00:34:36,934 --> 00:34:38,335
I'll get rid of everything.

777
00:34:40,270 --> 00:34:41,572
SHE CREATED A SAFE SPACE FOR THE BABY

778
00:34:41,638 --> 00:34:43,907
Are you feeling better now?

779
00:34:44,341 --> 00:34:45,509
THE ELDEST IS READY FOR A HAIRCUT

780
00:34:45,576 --> 00:34:47,444
How would you like your hair cut?

781
00:34:48,312 --> 00:34:51,782
- I just want a slight trim.
- Do you want to trim it?

782
00:34:52,316 --> 00:34:53,617
From this length...

783
00:34:53,684 --> 00:34:54,718
CHECKING THE CURRENT LENGTH

784
00:34:55,252 --> 00:34:56,753
Let me comb it through.

785
00:34:56,820 --> 00:34:58,522
HE CHECKS THE HAIR CONDITION

786
00:35:00,457 --> 00:35:02,726
It's thick and long.

787
00:35:03,160 --> 00:35:07,164
IT'S EXTREMELY CURLY AND THICK
EVEN AT A GLANCE

788
00:35:07,431 --> 00:35:09,299
Are you in middle school now?

789
00:35:09,366 --> 00:35:12,336
Yes, I'll be in seventh grade.

790
00:35:12,402 --> 00:35:14,004
- You're starting soon.
- Yes.

791
00:35:14,638 --> 00:35:16,573
IF HE'S STARTING MIDDLE SCHOOL

792
00:35:16,640 --> 00:35:19,142
Are there school rules about hair?

793
00:35:19,209 --> 00:35:20,777
- Not that I know of.
- Is that right?

794
00:35:21,078 --> 00:35:22,479
- Muju Middle School?
- Yes.

795
00:35:22,546 --> 00:35:24,514
HE'S GETTING A FRESH, NEW LOOK
FOR MIDDLE SCHOOL

796
00:35:24,581 --> 00:35:27,784
Then, I'll thin it out a bit
at this length.

797
00:35:27,851 --> 00:35:29,019
PRE-MIDDLE SCHOOL HAIRCUT

798
00:35:29,753 --> 00:35:33,256
- So are you the eldest?
- Yes.

799
00:35:33,323 --> 00:35:34,358
I am.

800
00:35:34,424 --> 00:35:36,793
SMALL TALK WHILE MISTING HIS HAIR

801
00:35:36,860 --> 00:35:39,830
- What's your name?
- Kim Seo-hyeon.

802
00:35:39,896 --> 00:35:41,131
- Seo-hyeon?
- Yes.

803
00:35:41,198 --> 00:35:42,466
So, you've lived

804
00:35:42,532 --> 00:35:44,735
- in Muju for 13 years?
- Yes.

805
00:35:45,035 --> 00:35:46,870
BIG REACTION

806
00:35:46,937 --> 00:35:49,172
So you're moving up to middle school.

807
00:35:49,239 --> 00:35:50,440
WELCOME TO THE MIDDLE SCHOOL WORLD

808
00:35:50,507 --> 00:35:51,975
Are you excited?

809
00:35:52,042 --> 00:35:53,677
- I am.
- You are?

810
00:35:55,012 --> 00:35:57,848
How did you know
there was a barbershop here?

811
00:35:58,315 --> 00:35:59,416
I looked up

812
00:35:59,750 --> 00:36:06,823
your Instagram story
and I found out it opened here.

813
00:36:07,524 --> 00:36:08,792
I see.

814
00:36:08,859 --> 00:36:13,063
- Does that mean you follow me?
- I do.

815
00:36:13,130 --> 00:36:14,164
- Really?
- Yes.

816
00:36:14,231 --> 00:36:15,732
Thank you so much.

817
00:36:15,799 --> 00:36:17,200
HE'S QUIET
BUT HE'S ACTUALLY A FAN

818
00:36:17,701 --> 00:36:18,802
Is it okay

819
00:36:19,703 --> 00:36:22,005
- if I trim it up neatly?
- Yes.

820
00:36:22,072 --> 00:36:25,475
Is there a haircut
that you specifically want to avoid?

821
00:36:25,542 --> 00:36:27,944
- As long as it's not too short.
- Will that be okay?

822
00:36:28,011 --> 00:36:29,346
GOT IT

823
00:36:29,413 --> 00:36:31,948
Okay, from this length...

824
00:36:32,482 --> 00:36:34,551
I'll go ahead and cut it.

825
00:36:38,922 --> 00:36:42,259
How should I cut the back?
I'm not sure.

826
00:36:42,959 --> 00:36:45,095
THINKING

827
00:36:45,762 --> 00:36:48,865
HE SHORTENS THE LENGTH FIRST

828
00:36:53,704 --> 00:36:55,138
EVEN AFTER WETTING

829
00:36:55,205 --> 00:36:58,408
HIS HAIR KEEPS PUFFING UP
DUE TO THICKNESS AND CURLS

830
00:36:59,009 --> 00:37:00,711
HE STOPS USING THE SCISSORS

831
00:37:00,777 --> 00:37:03,480
AND STARTS MISTING IT AGAIN

832
00:37:04,681 --> 00:37:07,117
MISTING

833
00:37:07,184 --> 00:37:10,554
MISTING AGAIN

834
00:37:11,088 --> 00:37:13,223
MISTING ENDLESSLY

835
00:37:13,590 --> 00:37:16,093
HIS HAIR IS SO THICK
THAT THE STIFFNESS WON'T DIE

836
00:37:16,560 --> 00:37:18,695
TORN

837
00:37:19,296 --> 00:37:20,964
Since you're going to middle school

838
00:37:21,865 --> 00:37:25,635
- can I trim it some more?
- Yes.

839
00:37:26,236 --> 00:37:27,938
- I'll go a bit bold.
- Sure.

840
00:37:28,004 --> 00:37:29,539
HE NEEDS TO BOLDLY THIN IT OUT FIRST

841
00:37:30,440 --> 00:37:34,945
BOSS PARK CHOOSES A HAIR CLIPPER

842
00:37:35,846 --> 00:37:41,785
A CLIPPER IS BETTER THAN SCISSORS
TO DEFINE THE LINE FOR THICK HAIR

843
00:37:43,320 --> 00:37:45,255
I'll keep going.

844
00:37:45,322 --> 00:37:49,359
HE RUNS IT THROUGH HIS HAIR
MULTIPLE TIMES, STANDING ON HIS FEET

845
00:37:50,527 --> 00:37:52,229
CLIPPING

846
00:37:53,163 --> 00:37:55,465
HE CLIPS HIS HAIR NONSTOP
AFTER THE NONSTOP MISTING

847
00:37:55,532 --> 00:37:56,533
FOCUSED

848
00:37:57,100 --> 00:38:00,036
AFTER A LONG TIME OF THINNING

849
00:38:00,637 --> 00:38:03,840
THE BACK OF HIS HEAD IS FINALLY NEAT

850
00:38:04,307 --> 00:38:07,010
SATISFIED

851
00:38:07,611 --> 00:38:11,782
HE DOES THE SIDES NOW

852
00:38:13,750 --> 00:38:17,087
The sides cover my ears too much.

853
00:38:17,154 --> 00:38:19,623
Could you cut it
just enough to uncover my ears?

854
00:38:19,689 --> 00:38:20,791
- Is it what you want?
- Yes.

855
00:38:20,857 --> 00:38:21,858
All right.

856
00:38:21,925 --> 00:38:23,126
THE QUIET FIRSTBORN
STILL SPEAKS HIS MIND

857
00:38:23,927 --> 00:38:26,263
REQUEST ACCEPTED

858
00:38:27,430 --> 00:38:30,901
HE GOES SILENT
AFTER SPEAKING HIS MIND

859
00:38:31,868 --> 00:38:35,272
What's your favorite subject
at school?

860
00:38:36,606 --> 00:38:39,142
Social studies.

861
00:38:39,209 --> 00:38:40,243
- Social studies?
- Yes.

862
00:38:40,777 --> 00:38:42,746
That's the subject
you're most interested in?

863
00:38:42,813 --> 00:38:43,880
IT'S A PRETTY SERIOUS SUBJECT

864
00:38:44,247 --> 00:38:47,951
- Like economics and stuff?
- Yes.

865
00:38:48,451 --> 00:38:50,453
Modern society
and contemporary society?

866
00:38:50,520 --> 00:38:51,621
Yes.

867
00:38:52,789 --> 00:38:54,524
- Do you also like Korean history?
- Yes.

868
00:38:55,125 --> 00:38:56,359
That's awesome.

869
00:38:56,426 --> 00:38:59,796
HAIRCUT DIFFICULTY: HIGH
COMMUNICATION DIFFICULTY: EXTREME

870
00:39:00,664 --> 00:39:04,668
CAUTIOUS

871
00:39:05,268 --> 00:39:08,138
HE KEEPS A POKER FACE,
EVEN WITH THE BUZZING CLIPPER

872
00:39:08,205 --> 00:39:11,808
UNFAZED

873
00:39:12,676 --> 00:39:16,179
ONLY THE LOUD CLIPPER FILLS THE ROOM

874
00:39:16,780 --> 00:39:19,049
IS HE OKAY?

875
00:39:19,449 --> 00:39:21,351
- It doesn't hurt, does it?
- No.

876
00:39:24,955 --> 00:39:27,157
FOCUSED

877
00:39:27,624 --> 00:39:30,427
HE CAREFULLY CUT THE SIDES, PAYING
ATTENTION TO LENGTH AS REQUESTED

878
00:39:31,561 --> 00:39:33,597
NEAT

879
00:39:34,231 --> 00:39:36,800
Once I finish cutting,
I'll part it over.

880
