- I bet it did. His neck too.

1487
01:04:41,303 --> 01:04:43,805
LINT ROLLER AND SPONGE

1488
01:04:44,406 --> 01:04:47,976
- Should we do it while he's groggy?
- You think so?

1489
01:04:48,443 --> 01:04:49,444
I'll hold him.

1490
01:04:50,078 --> 01:04:51,179
He woke up!

1491
01:04:51,546 --> 01:04:53,582
- Did he?
- He's up.

1492
01:04:54,015 --> 01:04:55,217
WHAT HAPPENED WHILE I WAS ASLEEP?

1493
01:04:55,283 --> 01:04:56,952
Good boy.

1494
01:04:57,018 --> 01:04:59,354
What's this? Look.

1495
01:04:59,921 --> 01:05:01,189
- It was easy, right?
- Well done!

1496
01:05:01,256 --> 01:05:03,325
- Well done.
- You held out so well.

1497
01:05:03,392 --> 01:05:04,526
Is the haircut over?

1498
01:05:05,093 --> 01:05:06,261
He does look cute.

1499
01:05:06,328 --> 01:05:07,863
HE LOOKS CUTER WITH NEAT BANGS

1500
01:05:07,929 --> 01:05:09,131
We fought back tears.

1501
01:05:09,197 --> 01:05:12,000
HE COMPLETED THE DIFFICULT HAIRCUT
FOR THE YOUNGEST CUSTOMER

1502
01:05:12,067 --> 01:05:13,235
Look.

1503
01:05:13,301 --> 01:05:15,070
His hair looks different.

1504
01:05:15,137 --> 01:05:17,606
- He's way cuter, isn't he?
- He is.

1505
01:05:17,672 --> 01:05:19,007
So pretty.

1506
01:05:19,841 --> 01:05:20,909
Yes?

1507
01:05:20,976 --> 01:05:21,977
HE SMILES AT HER PRAISE

1508
01:05:22,043 --> 01:05:25,981
- He must be in a good mood.
- Your compliments make him smile.

1509
01:05:26,681 --> 01:05:28,850
I took too long cutting his hair.

1510
01:05:29,251 --> 01:05:30,252
It's...

1511
01:05:30,318 --> 01:05:31,420
IT'S ALREADY LUNCHTIME

1512
01:05:32,120 --> 01:05:33,288
Hey.

1513
01:05:33,355 --> 01:05:35,323
Seon-hui, did you say
you only had breakfast?

1514
01:05:35,390 --> 01:05:36,691
- Yes.
- I didn't even have breakfast.

1515
01:05:36,758 --> 01:05:38,727
- I only had breakfast.
- Do you want some food?

1516
01:05:38,794 --> 01:05:40,462
- Yes, please.
- Do you want fried chicken?

1517
01:05:40,529 --> 01:05:41,930
- Fried chicken?
- That sounds tasty.

1518
01:05:43,031 --> 01:05:44,366
FRIED CHICKEN?

1519
01:05:44,833 --> 01:05:46,101
- Go play.
- Okay.

1520
01:05:47,002 --> 01:05:49,037
Should we have the brothers eat, too?

1521
01:05:49,104 --> 01:05:50,572
- The fried chicken.
- Yes, I'll make plenty.

1522
01:05:52,674 --> 01:05:56,178
SUDDENLY MAKING
9 SERVINGS OF FRIED CHICKEN?

1523
01:05:57,412 --> 01:06:00,549
HIS FIRST TIME MAKING 9 SERVINGS
CAN HE PULL THIS OFF?

1524
01:06:00,615 --> 01:06:03,485
LOTS

1525
01:06:04,152 --> 01:06:07,656
HE MOVES QUICKLY
TO FEED THEM FRESHLY FRIED CHICKEN

1526
01:06:08,690 --> 01:06:11,860
STARTING WITH THE SAUCE

1527
01:06:12,394 --> 01:06:14,529
MIXING

1528
01:06:15,163 --> 01:06:17,766
CHEF KWAK COATED THE CHICKEN
IN NO TIME

1529
01:06:18,266 --> 01:06:20,869
WHAT'S THIS SMELL?

1530
01:06:21,536 --> 01:06:22,971
SNIFFING

1531
01:06:23,038 --> 01:06:24,940
I smell delicious soy sauce.

1532
01:06:25,006 --> 01:06:26,441
- That's right.
- Are you making the sauce?

1533
01:06:26,508 --> 01:06:27,876
Correct.

1534
01:06:27,943 --> 01:06:29,911
May I come in and watch?

1535
01:06:29,978 --> 01:06:32,614
Yes, but first,
go wash your hands in the bathroom.

1536
01:06:32,681 --> 01:06:34,316
Okay!

1537
01:06:35,417 --> 01:06:36,918
As your cooking assistant.

1538
01:06:36,985 --> 01:06:38,854
THE ASSISTANT GOES TO WASH HANDS

1539
01:06:39,488 --> 01:06:40,989
I must maintain cleanliness.

1540
01:06:41,823 --> 01:06:42,858
This is

1541
01:06:43,225 --> 01:06:45,360
- potato starch.
- Potato starch.

1542
01:06:45,427 --> 01:06:47,362
I'm coating the chicken with it.

1543
01:06:48,330 --> 01:06:49,698
It's hot, so stand back.

1544
01:06:49,764 --> 01:06:50,932
Be careful.

1545
01:06:51,433 --> 01:06:52,901
You be careful first.

1546
01:06:53,468 --> 01:06:55,036
- Seriously, be careful.
- It's getting cooked.

1547
01:06:55,370 --> 01:06:56,838
Roll your sleeves down.

1548
01:06:57,706 --> 01:06:58,773
It's hot.

1549
01:06:58,840 --> 01:06:59,975
SHE WORRIES HE MIGHT GET INJURED

1550
01:07:00,041 --> 01:07:02,611
This side is down, but that side...
Oh, no, you got burned.

1551
01:07:03,144 --> 01:07:04,212
What's this?

1552
01:07:04,279 --> 01:07:07,015
- This is from...
- It's from cooking, right?

1553
01:07:07,082 --> 01:07:09,518
I don't even know.
I somehow get hurt when I'm here.

1554
01:07:09,985 --> 01:07:13,421
Cuts just somehow appear
when you're cooking.

1555
01:07:14,122 --> 01:07:15,423
PEEKING

1556
01:07:15,790 --> 01:07:17,559
WOW

1557
01:07:18,660 --> 01:07:20,896
Looking at this makes my head spin.

1558
01:07:20,962 --> 01:07:22,364
- The dirty dishes?
- Yes.

1559
01:07:22,430 --> 01:07:23,431
Same here.

1560
01:07:24,165 --> 01:07:25,634
It's hard for me to look at those.

1561
01:07:25,700 --> 01:07:27,202
THE COOKING CLUB PAIR GETS ALONG WELL

1562
01:07:28,270 --> 01:07:31,439
CRYING

1563
01:07:32,274 --> 01:07:33,508
HE MOVES FASTER AT THE BABY'S CRY

1564
01:07:33,575 --> 01:07:34,809
Careful.

1565
01:07:36,077 --> 01:07:37,512
THINKING

1566
01:07:37,579 --> 01:07:40,282
You don't want to stir it too much
when you're deep-frying.

1567
01:07:40,348 --> 01:07:42,117
- It gets disturbed.
- Oh, should I leave it alone?

1568
01:07:42,183 --> 01:07:43,518
- Yes, leave it alone.
- Okay.

1569
01:07:43,585 --> 01:07:45,186
It's boiling,
so it'll take care of itself.

1570
01:07:45,253 --> 01:07:46,454
I believe in you.

1571
01:07:46,521 --> 01:07:47,822
RELIABLE ADVICE FOR SOME REASON

1572
01:07:47,889 --> 01:07:49,691
Starch is tricky to handle.

1573
01:07:51,192 --> 01:07:52,794
You must be really good
at cooking, Seon-hui.

1574
01:07:54,229 --> 01:07:58,199
- I've been cooking since I was 8.
- That's awesome.

1575
01:07:58,733 --> 01:07:59,968
You're incredible.

1576
01:08:00,035 --> 01:08:01,937
SHE ALREADY HAS 5 YEARS OF EXPERIENCE
BY HELPING OUT HER GRANDMA

1577
01:08:02,003 --> 01:08:03,538
- Can I put it here?
- Yes.

1578
01:08:03,605 --> 01:08:08,276
FOLLOWING THE SENIOR COOK'S ADVICE

1579
01:08:09,911 --> 01:08:13,815
THE CHICKEN HAS TURNED GOLDEN-BROWN

1580
01:08:13,882 --> 01:08:16,184
- And the base...
- Taste it. It's hot.

1581
01:08:16,251 --> 01:08:17,719
TASTE IT

1582
01:08:18,620 --> 01:08:20,388
Take your time. It's hot.

1583
01:08:21,256 --> 01:08:24,960
TAKING A CAUTIOUS BITE

1584
01:08:25,026 --> 01:08:26,127
- It's good.
- You think so?

1585
01:08:26,194 --> 01:08:28,129
Yes, it's good. It's really tasty.

1586
01:08:28,196 --> 01:08:29,297
IT'S JUST WHAT SHE LIKES

1587
01:08:29,364 --> 01:08:32,067
Chef Yoon Nam-no made it for us.

1588
01:08:32,133 --> 01:08:33,134
BRAGGING ABOUT HIS MASTER

1589
01:08:33,201 --> 01:08:35,403
- It's seasoned.
- Yes, it's seasoned.

1590
01:08:36,237 --> 01:08:37,272
It tastes great.

1591
01:08:38,640 --> 01:08:40,342
I see you can tell
when the food is good.

1592
01:08:42,243 --> 01:08:43,678
The kids will love it.

1593
01:08:46,014 --> 01:08:49,384
EVEN THE SENIOR COOK
ACKNOWLEDGED THE GOOD TASTE

1594
01:08:51,720 --> 01:08:53,855
I think it would go well
with a mayonnaise dip.

1595
01:08:54,623 --> 01:08:56,491
- What?
- I think it would be nice

1596
01:08:56,558 --> 01:08:58,627
to serve it with a mayonnaise dip.

1597
01:08:58,693 --> 01:09:00,295
- Can you make that?
- Yes.

1598
01:09:01,129 --> 01:09:03,665
- Do you have ramyeon seasoning?
- Yes, we do.

1599
01:09:05,066 --> 01:09:06,468
Then I'll make the dip.

1600
01:09:06,534 --> 01:09:09,104
- Do you have sugar, too?
- Then look around

1601
01:09:09,170 --> 01:09:10,639
and see what's in the pantry.

1602
01:09:11,306 --> 01:09:12,407
Bring what you need.

1603
01:09:15,777 --> 01:09:16,778
Goodness.

1604
01:09:17,078 --> 01:09:19,247
What fifth-grader
knows how to make a mayo dip?

1605
01:09:21,950 --> 01:09:23,051
Unbelievable.

1606
01:09:23,118 --> 01:09:24,352
AMUSED

1607
01:09:24,953 --> 01:09:26,721
AN ARMFUL OF INGREDIENTS

1608
01:09:27,522 --> 01:09:29,824
I'll make it
with these three ingredients.

1609
01:09:29,891 --> 01:09:31,226
No, there are four.

1610
01:09:31,292 --> 01:09:32,594
MAYONNAISE, RAMYEON SEASONING,
LEMON JUICE, SUGAR

1611
01:09:32,661 --> 01:09:34,029
- Sugar too?
- Yes.

1612
01:09:37,465 --> 01:09:39,167
I wonder if it'll taste okay.

1613
01:09:43,538 --> 01:09:47,876
A LOT OF CREAMY MAYONNAISE

1614
01:09:47,942 --> 01:09:49,811
The chicken's a bit salty.

1615
01:09:49,878 --> 01:09:51,946
I'll make a slightly greasy dip.

1616
01:09:53,381 --> 01:09:54,916
A SPOONFUL OF SWEET SUGAR

1617
01:09:54,983 --> 01:09:57,318
No leftovers or Granny will scold me.

1618
01:10:00,522 --> 01:10:03,925
THE SECRET TO SEON-HUI'S MAYO DIP

1619
01:10:03,992 --> 01:10:08,196
I only need the seasoning.
You can use the noodles elsewhere.

1620
01:10:08,897 --> 01:10:11,833
SHE'S FRUGAL FOR A FIFTH-GRADER

1621
01:10:12,867 --> 01:10:17,405
ADDING THE RAMYEON SEASONING

1622
01:10:17,472 --> 01:10:19,574
Just enough lemon juice
that it doesn't stand out.

1623
01:10:20,108 --> 01:10:21,109
How does the top...

1624
01:10:22,577 --> 01:10:23,712
Oh, really?

1625
01:10:23,778 --> 01:10:25,180
SQUEEZE

1626
01:10:26,681 --> 01:10:28,349
IT'S DONE

1627
01:10:29,651 --> 01:10:31,152
TASTING IT LIKE A CHEF
WITH A DAB ON HER FINGER!

1628
01:10:31,219 --> 01:10:32,954
A SLIGHT TASTE

1629
01:10:33,021 --> 01:10:34,355
It tastes good.

1630
01:10:35,156 --> 01:10:36,357
It's good.

1631
01:10:36,991 --> 01:10:38,593
I did it. It's a success.

1632
01:10:38,660 --> 01:10:39,994
- Is it a success?
- Yes.

1633
01:10:41,096 --> 01:10:42,497
You got it in one try?

1634
01:10:43,798 --> 01:10:44,933
Good for you.

1635
01:10:45,967 --> 01:10:48,470
- Let Uncle BO GUM taste it.
- Uncle.

1636
01:10:49,304 --> 01:10:52,006
SETTING OFF CONFIDENTLY

1637
01:10:52,073 --> 01:10:54,309
I made a dip. Will you try it?

1638
01:10:55,143 --> 01:10:56,478
It looks nice.

1639
01:10:57,946 --> 01:10:59,714
It's for the fried chicken.

1640
01:11:01,049 --> 01:11:02,884
- It's so sour.
- I added lemon juice.

1641
01:11:03,485 --> 01:11:04,652
Looks good.

1642
01:11:06,321 --> 01:11:08,156
It's a dip for the fried chicken.

1643
01:11:09,390 --> 01:11:12,060
- It's so sour.
- I added lemon juice.

1644
01:11:12,127 --> 01:11:14,295
IT'S SO SOUR SHE CAN'T OPEN HER EYES

1645
01:11:14,362 --> 01:11:15,764
Thank you.

1646
01:11:17,365 --> 01:11:18,666
That jolted me awake.

1647
01:11:19,901 --> 01:11:21,269
I need to stay alert.

1648
01:11:23,538 --> 01:11:24,606
Okay, it's a success.

1649
01:11:25,340 --> 01:11:26,508
I got a good response.

1650
01:11:26,841 --> 01:11:28,109
- Did they give a good response?
- Yes.

1651
01:11:28,176 --> 01:11:29,711
They said it's nice and sour.

1652
01:11:31,946 --> 01:11:36,117
CHEF SEON-HUI IS SATISFIED

1653
01:11:37,185 --> 01:11:39,187
TO SERVE THE KIDS HOT CHICKEN

1654
01:11:40,655 --> 01:11:42,991
HE WORKS WITH TWO PANS

1655
01:11:43,057 --> 01:11:46,394
USING TIPS HE LEARNED
FROM CHEF YOON NAM-NO

1656
01:11:46,895 --> 01:11:49,397
SOUTHEAST ASIAN-STYLE GARLIC CHICKEN

1657
01:11:50,198 --> 01:11:52,400
CRISPY AND CRUNCHY

1658
01:11:52,467 --> 01:11:53,601
Are you done cutting their hair?

1659
01:11:54,269 --> 01:11:55,770
- Only Tae-eun's left.
- Just Tae-eun?

1660
01:11:56,504 --> 01:11:58,106
Will you do it now? Or after lunch?

1661
01:11:58,173 --> 01:12:00,041
- Let's do it after lunch.
- Okay.

1662
01:12:00,108 --> 01:12:01,509
- Let's eat together.
- Yes, let's eat now.

1663
01:12:01,576 --> 01:12:04,512
THEY'LL CUT THE HAIR
OF THE SECONDBORN AFTER LUNCH!

1664
01:12:04,579 --> 01:12:05,914
Let's eat!

1665
01:12:05,980 --> 01:12:09,117
- Let's eat, guys.
- Come and eat!

1666
01:12:09,184 --> 01:12:11,452
ALONG WITH HEALTHY VEGGIES
A SPECIAL DISH FOR THE KIDS!

1667
01:12:11,519 --> 01:12:13,988
The art group can sit here.

1668
01:12:15,089 --> 01:12:16,491
The art group. Come over here.

1669
01:12:16,558 --> 01:12:18,593
- I'll sit here.
- Sit there on the floor.

1670
01:12:18,660 --> 01:12:21,362
- We're one massive family.
- We are.

1671
01:12:21,429 --> 01:12:22,564
THE ROOM IS FULL OF KIDS

1672
01:12:22,630 --> 01:12:24,766
- What's this?
- I like being around lots of people.

1673
01:12:24,833 --> 01:12:27,468
- Do you like this? So do I.
- Yes. I like a crowd.

1674
01:12:28,469 --> 01:12:30,505
He's watching me intensely.

1675
01:12:30,572 --> 01:12:31,639
TAKING A BITE
WITH THE YOUNGEST IN HIS ARMS

1676
01:12:32,440 --> 01:12:34,843
CHEWING

1677
01:12:34,909 --> 01:12:36,177
It's delicious.

1678
01:12:37,312 --> 01:12:38,780
Can the baby have some chicken?

1679
01:12:38,847 --> 01:12:40,148
GASP!

1680
01:12:40,215 --> 01:12:41,749
It tastes exactly like that chicken.

1681
01:12:41,816 --> 01:12:43,084
INCREDIBLE

1682
01:12:43,785 --> 01:12:44,919
FRESHLY FRIED CHICKEN IS A RARE TREAT

1683
01:12:44,986 --> 01:12:47,188
Dong-yeon, did you
fry the chicken yourself?

1684
01:12:47,255 --> 01:12:49,357
- Eat. Go on. You're the eldest.
- Dig in.

1685
01:12:49,424 --> 01:12:50,625
What did you say your name was?

1686
01:12:50,692 --> 01:12:52,527
- He's Seo-hyeon.
- Seo-hyeon.

1687
01:12:54,229 --> 01:12:56,164
The dip is really nice, Seon-hui.

1688
01:12:57,365 --> 01:12:59,534
It tastes
just like ramyeon seasoning.

1689
01:12:59,601 --> 01:13:00,602
Isn't it nice?

1690
01:13:00,668 --> 01:13:01,669
PROUD

1691
01:13:02,036 --> 01:13:04,105
- Eat. Go on. You're the eldest.
- Dig in.

1692
01:13:04,172 --> 01:13:05,707
What did you say your name was?

1693
01:13:05,773 --> 01:13:07,575
- He's Seo-hyeon.
- Seo-hyeon.

1694
01:13:08,176 --> 01:13:09,510
Are you in middle school?

1695
01:13:09,577 --> 01:13:11,813
- He starts in March.
- I see.

1696
01:13:11,880 --> 01:13:13,615
ANSWERING FOR HIM

1697
01:13:14,249 --> 01:13:17,085
7TH GRADER SEO-HYEON
MAY BE SHY BUT HE LOVES THE CHICKEN

1698
01:13:17,852 --> 01:13:19,487
- Is it good?
- I've never had anything like this.

1699
01:13:19,554 --> 01:13:20,889
NODDING

1700
01:13:20,955 --> 01:13:22,857
I've never had anything like this.

1701
01:13:22,924 --> 01:13:24,359
- You want water?
- We need more water.

1702
01:13:24,425 --> 01:13:26,127
I'll get you more water
if you want some.

1703
01:13:26,194 --> 01:13:27,362
Okay. The water...

1704
01:13:28,630 --> 01:13:31,633
THEIR FIRST TIME EATING LUNCH
WITH THE LOCALS

1705
01:13:31,900 --> 01:13:34,202
Guys, you need to eat
lots of veggies, too.

1706
01:13:35,303 --> 01:13:37,138
Eat a lot of lettuce.

1707
01:13:37,505 --> 01:13:39,507
SILENCE

1708
01:13:41,509 --> 01:13:43,244
I think I spoke loud enough.

1709
01:13:44,412 --> 01:13:45,880
I heard you.

1710
01:13:46,881 --> 01:13:47,882
It tastes good.

1711
01:13:47,949 --> 01:13:50,084
EVERYONE'S TOO BUSY EATING CHICKEN

1712
01:13:50,151 --> 01:13:53,488
- Eat some veggies.
- Okay, I already did.

1713
01:13:55,723 --> 01:13:57,125
HERE'S SOMEONE WHO'S BUSIER

1714
01:13:57,191 --> 01:13:58,393
You can't eat this.

1715
01:13:58,459 --> 01:14:01,763
This is too sour for you.

1716
01:14:07,535 --> 01:14:11,239
NOT ONLY DOES HE HAVE TO EAT

1717
01:14:11,306 --> 01:14:14,943
AND HE HAS TO WATCH A BABY

1718
01:14:15,009 --> 01:14:17,312
Please wash your hands, Uncle.

1719
01:14:19,380 --> 01:14:23,751
HE FEEDS HIM, TOO

1720
01:14:23,818 --> 01:14:25,386
We're both part-timers here, too.

1721
01:14:26,621 --> 01:14:30,391
He doesn't cry anymore.
He must've gotten used to us.

1722
01:14:30,458 --> 01:14:34,162
BOSS PARK PLAYS WITH THE YOUNGEST
WHILE THE ELDEST EATS

1723
01:14:34,896 --> 01:14:39,167
HE EVEN STOPPED EATING
TO PLAY WITH A MIRROR

1724
01:14:39,233 --> 01:14:40,868
He's in a good mood now.

1725
01:14:40,935 --> 01:14:42,637
UNCLE BO GUM PUT THE YOUNGEST
IN A GOOD MOOD

1726
01:14:43,104 --> 01:14:45,707
ENTERTAINING THE BABY

1727
01:14:45,773 --> 01:14:47,008
THE UNCLES MAKE HIM REALLY HAPPY

1728
01:14:47,075 --> 01:14:48,309
He's clapping.

1729
01:14:49,277 --> 01:14:50,511
An explosion of applause.

1730
01:14:54,315 --> 01:15:01,322
FRIED CHICKEN TASTES EXTRA GOOD
WHEN EATEN TOGETHER

1731
01:15:03,825 --> 01:15:06,794
- I've had enough.
- You can leave it if you're full.

1732
01:15:07,562 --> 01:15:09,897
THE SECOND ATE IN A HURRY
BECAUSE HE WAS HUNGRY

1733
01:15:09,964 --> 01:15:11,165
WAIT!

1734
01:15:11,232 --> 01:15:13,067
Where are you going?

1735
01:15:13,134 --> 01:15:14,936
- Are you off to paint?
- No.

1736
01:15:15,003 --> 01:15:17,538
- To get your hair cut? Oh, okay.
- To the couch.

1737
01:15:17,605 --> 01:15:19,507
Tae-eun, you need a haircut, too.

1738
01:15:19,574 --> 01:15:21,309
- I know.
- You do?

1739
01:15:23,144 --> 01:15:26,614
I NEED TO GIVE HIM A HAIRCUT

1740
01:15:27,548 --> 01:15:28,916
YOU DON'T HAVE TO FINISH IT
IF YOU'RE FULL

1741
01:15:30,485 --> 01:15:31,986
TURNING TO LOOK AGAIN

1742
01:15:32,620 --> 01:15:36,958
HE'S STANDING AS IF HE'S BORED

1743
01:15:39,327 --> 01:15:40,461
Tae-eun's hair...

1744
01:15:40,528 --> 01:15:42,997
I'm not done yet.
I haven't finished eating.

1745
01:15:45,166 --> 01:15:46,667
I'll cut your hair for you.

1746
01:15:46,734 --> 01:15:48,569
BOSS PARK STOPS MID-LUNCH
TO GO OVER TO THE SECOND CHILD

1747
01:15:49,037 --> 01:15:50,471
- Shall I cut it later?
- What?

1748
01:15:50,538 --> 01:15:51,806
Later... Do you want a break?

1749
01:15:51,873 --> 01:15:53,408
- Now.
- Shall I do it now?

1750
01:15:53,474 --> 01:15:55,209
- Yes.
- Okay. Come here.

1751
01:15:55,710 --> 01:15:57,745
HE FOLLOWS UNCLE BO GUM

1752
01:15:58,546 --> 01:16:02,283
HE PREPARES TO SERVE THE LAST
OF THE THREE BROTHERS

1753
01:16:03,051 --> 01:16:06,421
HE MOVES FAST AS THE BOY
HAS WAITED A LONG TIME

1754
01:16:06,487 --> 01:16:08,356
- Did you enjoy your food?
- Yes.

1755
01:16:12,160 --> 01:16:13,761
- Excuse me.
- Okay.

1756
01:16:15,797 --> 01:16:16,798
HOWEVER

1757
01:16:16,864 --> 01:16:18,066
Thank you.

1758
01:16:19,033 --> 01:16:21,235
TOUCHING HIS THROAT

1759
01:16:22,136 --> 01:16:24,005
HE LOOKS A BIT UNCOMFORTABLE

1760
01:16:24,072 --> 01:16:25,840
- What? Is it uncomfortable?
- It tickles.

1761
01:16:25,907 --> 01:16:27,075
It tickles?

1762
01:16:27,775 --> 01:16:29,577
It's done. This is the last step.

1763
01:16:29,644 --> 01:16:34,415
THE YOUNG BOY IS SENSITIVE
TO THE ITCHY SENSATION

1764
01:16:34,849 --> 01:16:38,319
- Do you have a ticklish neck?
- Yes. My neck is very ticklish.

1765
01:16:38,386 --> 01:16:39,954
I used to be like that, too.

1766
01:16:40,021 --> 01:16:41,622
It got better as I got older.

1767
01:16:43,891 --> 01:16:46,861
HAIRCUT:
AS LESS TICKLISH AS POSSIBLE

1768
01:16:47,995 --> 01:16:50,364
Don't worry, no, no, no

1769
01:16:51,799 --> 01:16:55,503
TAPPING WITH THE HAIR CLIPPER

1770
01:16:56,404 --> 01:16:57,939
WINCING

1771
01:16:58,005 --> 01:16:59,273
That tickles.

1772
01:17:00,374 --> 01:17:02,243
No, tell yourself it's not ticklish.

1773
01:17:02,310 --> 01:17:03,644
- It's not.
- It's not ticklish.

1774
01:17:03,711 --> 01:17:05,113
It's not ticklish.

1775
01:17:05,179 --> 01:17:06,948
I AM NOT TICKLISH

1776
01:17:08,983 --> 01:17:11,185
BUT...

1777
01:17:12,053 --> 01:17:16,257
HE KEEPS SQUIRMING

1778
01:17:16,757 --> 01:17:18,860
No. I can't cut your hair
if you keep moving.

1779
01:17:18,926 --> 01:17:22,363
- It's not ticklish.
- It's not ticklish.

1780
01:17:23,531 --> 01:17:24,899
It's not ticklish.

1781
01:17:25,933 --> 01:17:28,870
FLICKING THE CAPE
TO BEAT THE SENSATION

1782
01:17:29,437 --> 01:17:32,907
I CAN'T CUT HIS HAIR
IF HE'S LIKE THIS

1783
01:17:34,575 --> 01:17:35,610
Look at the floor.

1784
01:17:36,477 --> 01:17:37,512
Here goes.

1785
01:17:38,379 --> 01:17:41,382
HE DECIDES TO DO A QUICK SHAVE

1786
01:17:41,983 --> 01:17:45,586
MOVING FAST WITHOUT HESITATION

1787
01:17:46,454 --> 01:17:47,722
Can you look up?

1788
01:17:48,122 --> 01:17:49,390
Let's have a look.

1789
01:17:49,457 --> 01:17:52,460
HE MANAGED TO CUT
THE HAIR IN THE BACK

1790
01:17:53,094 --> 01:17:55,530
GLANCING BEHIND HIM

1791
01:17:55,596 --> 01:17:56,597
Isn't this fascinating?

1792
01:17:56,664 --> 01:18:00,601
BO GUM'S WORRIED ABOUT THE TWO
WHO ARE WAITING

1793
01:18:01,502 --> 01:18:03,137
You must want to leave already.

1794
01:18:03,204 --> 01:18:04,338
I'LL WORK AS FAST AS I CAN

1795
01:18:05,540 --> 01:18:07,875
THOSE IN THE RECEPTION ROOM
NOTICED THEM, TOO

1796
01:18:07,942 --> 01:18:09,844
THINKING

1797
01:18:11,379 --> 01:18:12,513
Seo-yul.

1798
01:18:12,580 --> 01:18:13,881
SANG-YI SUDDENLY COMES UP

1799
01:18:13,948 --> 01:18:15,016
Come here, Seo-yul.

1800
01:18:15,583 --> 01:18:18,052
Seo-yul, I'm... My stomach...

1801
01:18:18,586 --> 01:18:20,421
It's my stomach.

1802
01:18:20,488 --> 01:18:21,622
Seo-yul.

1803
01:18:21,689 --> 01:18:22,990
SHALL I SHOW YOU SOMETHING FUN?

1804
01:18:24,892 --> 01:18:27,795
A REPEAT OF THE CARD MAGIC SHOW

1805
01:18:28,863 --> 01:18:32,099
INTERESTED

1806
01:18:32,166 --> 01:18:33,267
That's it.

1807
01:18:33,668 --> 01:18:34,835
Tae-eun.

1808
01:18:34,902 --> 01:18:36,771
The chicken gave me a bellyache.

1809
01:18:39,073 --> 01:18:42,109
A SECOND REPEAT

1810
01:18:42,810 --> 01:18:45,046
IMPRESSED

1811
01:18:45,313 --> 01:18:47,782
THE PART-TIMER'S IMPRESSED, TOO

1812
01:18:48,683 --> 01:18:51,252
SATISFIED

1813
01:18:52,086 --> 01:18:53,688
- We're off now.
- Take care.

1814
01:18:53,754 --> 01:18:55,756
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

1815
01:18:55,823 --> 01:18:58,092
- Bye.
- Bye, Seon-hui and Da-in.

1816
01:18:58,159 --> 01:18:59,527
- Bye.
- Bye.

1817
01:18:59,594 --> 01:19:02,730
Look at this. What is this?

1818
01:19:02,797 --> 01:19:07,235
THE HAIRCUT IS STILL UNDERWAY

1819
01:19:08,102 --> 01:19:11,372
YAWNING

1820
01:19:11,439 --> 01:19:12,907
I'll do it for you, Seo-yul.

1821
01:19:14,008 --> 01:19:15,309
You did it, Seo-yul.

1822
01:19:16,077 --> 01:19:17,578
- Are you uncomfortable?
- No.

1823
01:19:17,645 --> 01:19:19,347
- Are you doing okay so far?
- Yes.

1824
01:19:22,783 --> 01:19:26,887
SOMEONE IS WATCHING THEM BOTH

1825
01:19:32,460 --> 01:19:34,462
Seo-hyeon looks like
he wants to go home soon.

1826
01:19:35,830 --> 01:19:37,531
- Tae-eun?
- Seo-hyeon.

1827
01:19:38,065 --> 01:19:39,267
We'll finish soon, Seo-hyeon.

1828
01:19:39,634 --> 01:19:41,402
- Sorry.
- I'm taking a while.

1829
01:19:42,236 --> 01:19:46,007
THE ELDEST HAS BEEN WAITING QUIETLY
FOR THREE HOURS

1830
01:19:47,275 --> 01:19:52,179
BO GUM HAS BEEN WORKING NONSTOP, TOO

1831
01:19:54,115 --> 01:19:56,617
GETTING ANXIOUS

1832
01:19:56,951 --> 01:19:58,886
- Are you all right?
- Yes.

1833
01:19:58,953 --> 01:20:00,321
Do you want a five-minute break?

1834
01:20:00,388 --> 01:20:03,924
No, then Tae-eun will get bored.

1835
01:20:03,991 --> 01:20:05,760
- He waited for too long.
- Okay.

1836
01:20:07,094 --> 01:20:10,631
LET'S SEE

1837
01:20:11,365 --> 01:20:16,437
SO-HYUN QUIETLY WATCHED BOSS PARK

1838
01:20:17,371 --> 01:20:23,778
SHE GETS SOMETHING FROM THE KITCHEN?

1839
01:20:25,613 --> 01:20:26,747
Short bangs in the front?

1840
01:20:27,948 --> 01:20:29,850
That length?
How about the sides and back?

1841
01:20:30,551 --> 01:20:32,320
- Thank you.
- Take a sip.

1842
01:20:33,554 --> 01:20:35,323
- Thank you.
- Take a sip.

1843
01:20:35,389 --> 01:20:38,259
You can cut it short.

1844
01:20:38,326 --> 01:20:40,094
SHE WAS SENSIBLE ENOUGH
TO GET BOSS PARK A COLD DRINK

1845
01:20:41,062 --> 01:20:42,396
Got it. That tastes good.

1846
01:20:45,166 --> 01:20:47,001
I'll leave your coffee here, Sang-yi.

1847
01:20:47,601 --> 01:20:49,837
Han-na, thank you.

1848
01:20:49,904 --> 01:20:51,439
SHE ALSO SERVED SANG-YI
WHO WAS BABYSITTING

1849
01:20:51,505 --> 01:20:52,840
Thanks, Han-na.

1850
01:20:54,041 --> 01:20:55,576
RETURNS TO THE KITCHEN
AFTER THE DELIVERY

1851
01:20:55,643 --> 01:20:56,844
Let's clean all this up.

1852
01:20:59,580 --> 01:21:01,782
A HEAP OF DISHES

1853
01:21:01,849 --> 01:21:02,850
Maybe not this.

1854
01:21:03,451 --> 01:21:05,353
- It's greasy.
- That's right.

1855
01:21:06,721 --> 01:21:09,857
LET'S GET STARTED WITH THE DISHES

1856
01:21:09,924 --> 01:21:11,258
It's completely soaked.

1857
01:21:11,325 --> 01:21:12,827
Hey, So-hyun, leave it.

1858
01:21:12,893 --> 01:21:14,628
- Why? I'll do the dishes.
- No, I'll do it.

1859
01:21:14,695 --> 01:21:16,697
No. You cooked.

1860
01:21:19,166 --> 01:21:23,337
SHE INSISTS ON DOING THE DISHES

1861
01:21:23,671 --> 01:21:26,207
BO GUM IS SPEEDING UP

1862
01:21:27,641 --> 01:21:29,043
Let's look outside, Seo-yul.

1863
01:21:29,110 --> 01:21:30,878
MEANWHILE, SANG-YI TAKES THE BABY

1864
01:21:31,846 --> 01:21:37,418
WALKING AROUND THE YARD,
TO CARE FOR THE 18-MONTH-OLD

1865
01:21:40,354 --> 01:21:41,489
What's that?

1866
01:21:42,223 --> 01:21:45,126
THEY EVEN TOUR THE ROOFTOP

1867
01:21:45,192 --> 01:21:46,293
Is it interesting?

1868
01:21:46,594 --> 01:21:47,895
What do you think, Seo-yul?

1869
01:21:49,897 --> 01:21:54,101
THEY RETURN AFTER THE SHORT WALK

1870
01:21:59,507 --> 01:22:03,177
NOW DONG-YEON TAKES OVER

1871
01:22:03,244 --> 01:22:04,578
Your big brother

1872
01:22:04,645 --> 01:22:07,415
is getting a haircut.

1873
01:22:07,481 --> 01:22:09,316
Your brother's getting a haircut.

1874
01:22:10,151 --> 01:22:14,355
TAE-EUN IS GETTING HIS BANGS TRIMMED

1875
01:22:21,295 --> 01:22:23,898
How come you're handsome
with such pretty double eyelids?

1876
01:22:26,100 --> 01:22:28,068
- I love his eyelashes, too.
- Yes.

1877
01:22:31,872 --> 01:22:33,274
Good job.

1878
01:22:34,041 --> 01:22:35,042
Thank you.

1879
01:22:35,109 --> 01:22:36,310
THE HAIRCUT IS FINALLY OVER

1880
01:22:36,377 --> 01:22:38,012
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

1881
01:22:39,146 --> 01:22:42,950
HIS BUSHY HAIR GOT CLEANED UP

1882
01:22:43,017 --> 01:22:45,619
- One, two, three.
- Can you see?

1883
01:22:46,987 --> 01:22:49,723
WITH THE THREE BROTHERS
WHO WAITED PATIENTLY FOR A LONG TIME

1884
01:22:49,890 --> 01:22:51,926
THE TWO YOUNGER BOYS ARE CHEERFUL

1885
01:22:52,293 --> 01:22:54,028
NOT ANGRY

1886
01:22:54,395 --> 01:22:56,597
- Let's go home!
- You're going home!

1887
01:22:57,398 --> 01:22:58,599
- Why are you crying?
- You won't go?

1888
01:22:59,066 --> 01:23:01,902
- Let's go home and play.
- Don't push me!

1889
01:23:01,969 --> 01:23:03,137
Get your hand out.

1890
01:23:03,204 --> 01:23:04,438
THE YOUNGEST GOT CLOSE
WITH THE UNCLES

1891
01:23:04,505 --> 01:23:06,240
Okay. Will you sit up for me?

1892
01:23:06,307 --> 01:23:07,408
LEANING BACK

1893
01:23:07,975 --> 01:23:09,076
Where's my jacket?

1894
01:23:09,443 --> 01:23:11,178
I'll bring it. I'll get it for you.

1895
01:23:11,812 --> 01:23:13,314
I found your hand.

1896
01:23:13,848 --> 01:23:15,683
That's it. You're all dressed.

1897
01:23:15,749 --> 01:23:17,017
We're done.

1898
01:23:17,084 --> 01:23:18,652
NOT AN EASY TASK TO SEND HIM HOME

1899
01:23:19,186 --> 01:23:20,521
A HELPER APPEARS TO GET THEM HOME

1900
01:23:20,588 --> 01:23:21,589
Eat this on your way home.

1901
01:23:22,022 --> 01:23:24,391
SHE GETS THE YOUNGEST BOY'S SHOES

1902
01:23:24,458 --> 01:23:26,026
Let's get your other hand out.

1903
01:23:26,093 --> 01:23:27,728
I'll hold him. Put on his shoes.

1904
01:23:29,063 --> 01:23:30,631
Put on your jacket.

1905
01:23:31,499 --> 01:23:32,867
That looks fun.

1906
01:23:32,933 --> 01:23:33,968
HELPING THE MIDDLE BOY DRESS

1907
01:23:34,034 --> 01:23:35,369
It makes a sound.

1908
01:23:35,436 --> 01:23:37,404
Come here.
When did your laces come untied?

1909
01:23:37,471 --> 01:23:38,939
Stick your foot out.

1910
01:23:39,673 --> 01:23:40,674
Stick out your foot.

1911
01:23:40,741 --> 01:23:42,042
It must've been a long day for you.

1912
01:23:42,543 --> 01:23:43,878
Go home and rest.

1913
01:23:46,547 --> 01:23:48,582
- Do you have everything?
- We're done.

1914
01:23:48,649 --> 01:23:50,518
This is a bit cold because it's wet.

1915
01:23:50,584 --> 01:23:51,619
GIGGLING

1916
01:23:51,685 --> 01:23:52,853
Bye, Seo-hyeon.

1917
01:23:52,920 --> 01:23:56,156
- Bye, Tae-eun.
- Seo-hyeon, Seo-yul, Tae-eun. Bye.

1918
01:23:56,223 --> 01:23:57,491
Bye!

1919
01:23:57,958 --> 01:24:00,227
Bye. Thank you, Tae-eun.

1920
01:24:00,794 --> 01:24:02,029
Good job.

1921
01:24:02,096 --> 01:24:05,866
PHEW

1922
01:24:07,668 --> 01:24:09,470
- Come here, So-hyun.
- Look at this.

1923
01:24:09,537 --> 01:24:12,239
- Thank you.
- Are you holding it in?

1924
01:24:12,306 --> 01:24:13,908
BOSS PARK FINALLY GETS A BREATHER

1925
01:24:14,608 --> 01:24:19,113
HE DIDN'T GET TO FINISH HIS LUNCH

1926
01:24:19,480 --> 01:24:22,049
- Is it that way?
- My gosh, the wind!

1927
01:24:22,116 --> 01:24:25,619
A ROWDY AND SUSPICIOUS GROUP
APPROACHES

1928
01:24:25,686 --> 01:24:28,923
You know,
I've never been to this barbershop.

1929
01:24:28,989 --> 01:24:31,125
- Neither have I.
- None of us has been here.

1930
01:24:31,191 --> 01:24:32,259
GIGGLING AS THEY HEAD
TO THE BARBERSHOP

1931
01:24:33,227 --> 01:24:37,631
BOSS PARK CAME OUT
TO SHAKE OUT THE CUTTING CAPE

1932
01:24:37,698 --> 01:24:39,233
We're just going there.

1933
01:24:40,000 --> 01:24:41,735
- Hello.
- Hello.

1934
01:24:42,102 --> 01:24:44,305
GASP

1935
01:24:45,573 --> 01:24:46,907
- What is this?
- Gosh.

1936
01:24:47,341 --> 01:24:49,310
I don't think
I can get my hair cut here.

1937
01:24:52,212 --> 01:24:54,448
We have a group of high school girls.

1938
01:24:57,284 --> 01:24:59,653
A LOT OF STUDENTS ARE VISITING TODAY
BECAUSE IT'S THE BREAK

1939
01:24:59,720 --> 01:25:01,088
- Hello.
- Do you want your hair done?

1940
01:25:01,155 --> 01:25:02,456
- Yes.
- Hello.

1941
01:25:02,523 --> 01:25:03,724
Hello!

1942
01:25:06,760 --> 01:25:10,097
OH, MY GOSH!

1943
01:25:10,664 --> 01:25:12,967
We came to get our hair cut.

1944
01:25:13,033 --> 01:25:14,134
Hang on.

1945
01:25:14,635 --> 01:25:16,937
Where do you live?

1946
01:25:17,004 --> 01:25:19,740
- I live here. Yes.
- In Apseom Village?

1947
01:25:19,807 --> 01:25:22,076
- And your friends?
- We live downtown.

1948
01:25:22,142 --> 01:25:24,178
- We came to see her.
- How old are you?

1949
01:25:24,244 --> 01:25:25,879
- I'm in 12th grade.
- A senior now.

1950
01:25:25,946 --> 01:25:27,448
- I'm in 10th grade.
- In 10th grade.

1951
01:25:27,514 --> 01:25:28,582
I see.

1952
01:25:28,649 --> 01:25:30,050
So there were

1953
01:25:30,117 --> 01:25:33,520
- high-schoolers in this village too.
- Yes.

1954
01:25:33,587 --> 01:25:35,723
- Who needs a cut?
- Just one person.

1955
01:25:35,789 --> 01:25:37,591
- Oh, okay.
- Sorry.

1956
01:25:37,658 --> 01:25:39,893
- Where can I put my bag?
- In here.

1957
01:25:40,427 --> 01:25:41,829
WHISPERING

1958
01:25:41,895 --> 01:25:42,930
SMACK

1959
01:25:42,997 --> 01:25:44,264
I don't think I can do this.

1960
01:25:45,399 --> 01:25:46,500
What should I do?

1961
01:25:50,371 --> 01:25:51,972
- Sit over here.
- Okay.

1962
01:25:53,140 --> 01:25:58,112
GIRLS HER AGE
CARE A LOT ABOUT THEIR LOOKS

1963
01:25:58,178 --> 01:26:02,182
BOSS PARK IS EXTRA CAUTIOUS

1964
01:26:02,249 --> 01:26:03,484
How do you want it done?

1965
01:26:03,550 --> 01:26:06,954
I want to make a donation.

1966
01:26:07,421 --> 01:26:08,956
- You're donating your hair?
- Yes.

1967
01:26:10,157 --> 01:26:11,725
She's donating her hair.

1968
01:26:12,860 --> 01:26:14,962
You want to donate your hair? Then...

1969
01:26:15,963 --> 01:26:17,865
Don't I need to cut off
about this much?

1970
01:26:17,931 --> 01:26:19,333
So...

1971
01:26:20,200 --> 01:26:25,072
The hair needs to be
at least 20 to 25cm long.

1972
01:26:25,139 --> 01:26:28,008
Have you always donated your hair?
Is this your first time?

1973
01:26:28,075 --> 01:26:32,079
It's not my first time.
I've done it once in middle school.

1974
01:26:32,413 --> 01:26:34,748
THIS 12TH GRADER
HAS DONATED HER HAIR BEFORE

1975
01:26:34,815 --> 01:26:38,385
I'm thinking of cutting off 25cm
and going for a bob.

1976
01:26:39,653 --> 01:26:43,023
BOSS PARK IS FACING A MISSION
WHERE HE MUST CUT OFF 25CM

1977
01:26:43,457 --> 01:26:45,292
I wonder if this is 25cm long.

1978
01:26:47,995 --> 01:26:50,698
- This much? Right to your chin?
- Yes.

1979
01:26:50,998 --> 01:26:53,333
Tie two ponytails at either side

1980
01:26:53,400 --> 01:26:56,537
leaving 25cm below the hair-tie
and cut above the elastic.

1981
01:26:56,603 --> 01:26:58,238
- You think so?
- That would make a sharp bob.

1982
01:26:58,305 --> 01:26:59,907
UNDERSTOOD

1983
01:27:02,776 --> 01:27:06,513
TYING HER HAIR
WITH ELASTIC BANDS AS SHE SAID

1984
01:27:07,014 --> 01:27:08,949
- About here?
- Yes.

1985
01:27:11,852 --> 01:27:13,020
The hair down here.

1986
01:27:13,520 --> 01:27:14,922
Is this even 20cm long?

1987
01:27:15,689 --> 01:27:19,393
- I'd say it's about 30cm.
- Oh, okay. Good.

1988
01:27:20,894 --> 01:27:22,062
We got it right.

1989
01:27:22,129 --> 01:27:23,330
THEY'VE DECIDED ON THE LENGTH

1990
01:27:23,597 --> 01:27:24,998
Right here? There's no going back.

1991
01:27:25,065 --> 01:27:26,266
- Does it look even?
- Yes.

1992
01:27:26,800 --> 01:27:28,769
- Are you... Are you okay with it?
- Yes.

1993
01:27:29,236 --> 01:27:30,871
- I'll cut it off, then.
- Yes.

1994
01:27:32,072 --> 01:27:33,774
- Are you ready?
- Yes.

1995
01:27:33,841 --> 01:27:34,875
TIME TO CUT IT FOR REAL

1996
01:27:35,442 --> 01:27:37,411
THE PART-TIMER ASSISTS

1997
01:27:38,212 --> 01:27:39,680
- Here goes. Yes.
- Here?

1998
01:27:40,848 --> 01:27:47,121
INSTEAD OF BEING THROWN OUT,
THIS HAIR WILL GO TO HELP SOMEONE

1999
01:27:47,855 --> 01:27:49,623
GETTING NERVOUS ALTOGETHER

2000
01:27:49,690 --> 01:27:50,758
FLINCH

2001
01:28:05,339 --> 01:28:07,441
IT'S HARD TO CUT THROUGH
A CLUMP OF HAIR

2002
01:28:07,508 --> 01:28:08,509
What?

2003
01:28:10,244 --> 01:28:11,311
It's not working.

2004
01:28:12,179 --> 01:28:14,014
IN THAT CASE

2005
01:28:14,081 --> 01:28:15,849
SAWING THROUGH

2006
01:28:16,617 --> 01:28:20,587
HE PUSHES GENTLY
AND THE HAIR FALLS AWAY

2007
01:28:21,121 --> 01:28:24,391
THE HAIR SHE GREW FOR A LONG TIME
FALLS AWAY IN AN INSTANT

2008
01:28:24,958 --> 01:28:26,160
Good.

2009
01:28:26,460 --> 01:28:28,162
- Here's one bundle.
- Okay.

2010
01:28:30,164 --> 01:28:32,599
NICE AND STRAIGHT

2011
01:28:33,033 --> 01:28:36,837
NOW FOR THE OTHER SIDE

2012
01:28:41,074 --> 01:28:44,311
SAME SAWING MOVEMENTS

2013
01:28:44,978 --> 01:28:48,282
THEY CUT THROUGH SMOOTHLY

2014
01:28:50,517 --> 01:28:51,718
That's it.

2015
01:28:53,253 --> 01:28:54,988
Short hair suits you well, too.

2016
01:28:55,055 --> 01:28:57,524
- Yes, you look good.
- Thank you.

2017
01:28:58,458 --> 01:28:59,893
- Sit back.
- Okay.

2018
01:29:00,761 --> 01:29:02,496
PLEASED

2019
01:29:03,096 --> 01:29:07,134
THE HAIR WILL BE
OF GREAT USE TO SOMEONE

2020
01:29:07,734 --> 01:29:10,571
- We should tell them this was nice.
- Gyu-ri cut her hair.

2021
01:29:10,637 --> 01:29:11,672
- Really?
- Yes.

2022
01:29:12,105 --> 01:29:13,874
LET'S SEE

2023
01:29:13,941 --> 01:29:15,809
Oh, Yang Gyu-ri.

2024
01:29:15,876 --> 01:29:17,978
- Doesn't she look nicer now?
- She looks like her sister.

2025
01:29:19,913 --> 01:29:21,215
You look like your sister.

2026
01:29:23,050 --> 01:29:24,284
It feels weird.

2027
01:29:24,351 --> 01:29:25,953
- You're pretty. It suits you.
- You think so?

2028
01:29:26,019 --> 01:29:27,187
- She looks good.
- Yes.

2029
01:29:30,457 --> 01:29:31,525
My gosh.

2030
01:29:32,125 --> 01:29:33,827
EMBARRASSED

2031
01:29:33,894 --> 01:29:36,763
You look very sophisticated.

2032
01:29:36,830 --> 01:29:38,665
- Doesn't it suit her well?
- Totally.

2033
01:29:39,032 --> 01:29:41,235
EVERYONE PRAISES THE TRANSFORMATION

2034
01:29:41,301 --> 01:29:43,904
- Did you grow your hair to donate?
- Yes.

2035
01:29:44,938 --> 01:29:46,773
That's so meaningful.

2036
01:29:47,808 --> 01:29:51,245
IT'S TIME TO STYLE THE BOB

2037
01:29:52,546 --> 01:29:56,583
If you're in 12th grade, you must
be thinking about your future.

2038
01:29:56,984 --> 01:29:58,085
CONCERNED ABOUT HER FUTURE PATH

2039
01:29:58,151 --> 01:29:59,319
- Yes.
- That's a concern.

2040
01:29:59,386 --> 01:30:01,555
I have kind of made up my mind.

2041
01:30:01,622 --> 01:30:03,257
- You have?
- Yes.

2042
01:30:03,857 --> 01:30:05,759
Can I ask what you plan to do?

2043
01:30:05,826 --> 01:30:07,127
Clinical pathology.

2044
01:30:07,361 --> 01:30:08,996
- Clinical pathology?
- Yes.

2045
01:30:09,463 --> 01:30:10,697
Gosh.

2046
01:30:11,231 --> 01:30:13,867
Seeing that you wanted
to donate your hair

2047
01:30:13,934 --> 01:30:17,738
made me think
you wanted to help others.

2048
01:30:17,804 --> 01:30:20,073
That's true. I think that's why

2049
01:30:20,140 --> 01:30:22,476
- I decided to go into health.
- Right.

2050
01:30:22,542 --> 01:30:26,346
I've never met someone who wanted
to study clinical pathology.

2051
01:30:27,047 --> 01:30:29,182
Then do you have

2052
01:30:30,217 --> 01:30:32,653
lots of friends
and a boyfriend perhaps?

2053
01:30:32,719 --> 01:30:34,321
Yes, I have a boyfriend.

2054
01:30:34,855 --> 01:30:36,423
GOODNESS

2055
01:30:36,490 --> 01:30:37,691
Good for you.

2056
01:30:38,992 --> 01:30:41,595
Did you meet your boyfriend
at school?

2057
01:30:41,962 --> 01:30:43,096
He's a year below me.

2058
01:30:43,397 --> 01:30:44,932
SHE'S DATING A YOUNGER GUY?

2059
01:30:46,199 --> 01:30:48,902
- Gyu-ri, you...
- You're dating a younger guy?

2060
01:30:48,969 --> 01:30:50,203
- My gosh.
- How did you meet?

2061
01:30:50,270 --> 01:30:51,438
Did she explain already?

2062
01:30:51,505 --> 01:30:52,773
I haven't heard how they met.

2063
01:30:52,839 --> 01:30:54,007
- Well...
- She didn't say.

2064
01:30:54,708 --> 01:30:57,511
- When the freshmen start school,
- Yes.

2065
01:30:57,577 --> 01:31:00,380
- the seniors go downstairs to look.
- Yes.

2066
01:31:00,447 --> 01:31:03,817
I noticed this guy whom I'd seen
in the corridor all the time.

2067
01:31:03,884 --> 01:31:05,319
I feel butterflies right now.

2068
01:31:05,385 --> 01:31:07,521
- I didn't think much at first.
- Okay.

2069
01:31:07,587 --> 01:31:09,756
But he had such a pretty smile.

2070
01:31:09,823 --> 01:31:12,392
- Hang on.
- So I wanted to get to know him.

2071
01:31:12,459 --> 01:31:13,460
OH, MY GOSH

2072
01:31:13,527 --> 01:31:16,463
- So I...
- I need to hide my expression.

2073
01:31:17,431 --> 01:31:19,366
I told a younger student I knew

2074
01:31:19,866 --> 01:31:23,337
that I wanted to get to know the guy.

2075
01:31:23,403 --> 01:31:26,640
That friend went and told him.

2076
01:31:26,707 --> 01:31:29,843
"A student a year above us
wants to get to know you."

2077
01:31:29,910 --> 01:31:32,379
- Yes, so...
- "She wants your number."

2078
01:31:32,446 --> 01:31:34,047
I didn't go that far.

2079
01:31:34,114 --> 01:31:35,816
I followed him on Instagram.

2080
01:31:36,450 --> 01:31:38,085
- And sent a DM.
- My word.

2081
01:31:38,151 --> 01:31:40,320
I said,
"You must've heard from so-and-so."

2082
01:31:40,387 --> 01:31:43,156
"I got in touch because I wanted
to get to know you."

2083
01:31:43,490 --> 01:31:45,692
- And he said
- How cool of you.

2084
01:31:45,759 --> 01:31:48,028
he was up
for getting to know me, too.

2085
01:31:48,095 --> 01:31:51,031
We started talking and met for walks

2086
01:31:51,098 --> 01:31:52,432
and then got together.

2087
01:31:53,800 --> 01:31:55,502
I'm so jealous.

2088
01:31:55,569 --> 01:31:57,070
What the heck?

2089
01:31:57,137 --> 01:32:00,474
What are you doing at school?
It's a place to study.

2090
01:32:01,041 --> 01:32:02,275
Honestly.

2091
01:32:03,276 --> 01:32:04,678
Have you been to Mount Deogyusan?

2092
01:32:04,745 --> 01:32:06,279
- I have.
- With your boyfriend?

2093
01:32:06,346 --> 01:32:07,347
No.

2094
01:32:07,681 --> 01:32:09,950
I went hiking
when I was in elementary school.

2095
01:32:10,017 --> 01:32:11,485
You should go with your boyfriend.

2096
01:32:11,551 --> 01:32:12,686
- With my boyfriend?
- Yes.

2097
01:32:12,753 --> 01:32:16,056
There's a thick blanket of snow,
and it's incredible.

2098
01:32:16,556 --> 01:32:18,458
You might end up promising
to be together forever.

2099
01:32:18,525 --> 01:32:20,427
- She can't.
- Why not?

2100
01:32:20,494 --> 01:32:21,728
It's too soon to say it's forever.

2101
01:32:21,795 --> 01:32:23,830
- It's possible.
- Why promise that now?

2102
01:32:23,897 --> 01:32:24,998
At this young age?

2103
01:32:25,065 --> 01:32:26,266
UNCLE IS AGAINST IT

2104
01:32:26,333 --> 01:32:28,835
- Do your parents know about him?
- Yes, they do.

2105
01:32:28,902 --> 01:32:29,903
UNBELIEVABLE

2106
01:32:30,137 --> 01:32:31,538
BACK TO CONCENTRATING ON THE CUT

2107
01:32:31,605 --> 01:32:33,607
- This category seems more popular.
- Right.

2108
01:32:34,207 --> 01:32:39,279
CLEANING UP THE ROUGH ENDS

2109
01:32:39,746 --> 01:32:41,982
ROLLING THE TIPS

2110
01:32:42,482 --> 01:32:45,285
CHECKING THE LENGTH ON EITHER SIDE

2111
01:32:45,852 --> 01:32:49,456
SHE GREW HER HAIR FOR A LONG TIME
TO BE ABLE TO DONATE IT

2112
01:32:49,856 --> 01:32:53,093
HE TAKES EXTRA CARE WITH THE CUT

2113
01:32:53,794 --> 01:32:56,096
THE SCISSORS ARE AT AN ANGLE?

2114
01:32:56,696 --> 01:32:59,666
HE'S CUTTING HER HAIR DIAGONALLY

2115
01:33:00,167 --> 01:33:06,506
IT'S NOT BOSS PARK'S USUAL TECHNIQUE

2116
01:33:06,573 --> 01:33:07,607
Goodness.

2117
01:33:08,308 --> 01:33:10,811
I cut your hair so it slants forward.

2118
01:33:10,877 --> 01:33:12,712
- Okay.
- Turn your head. Look to the right.

2119
01:33:12,779 --> 01:33:16,183
- Oh, I think it looks nice.
- This is one possible style.

2120
01:33:17,250 --> 01:33:20,854
Or we can keep the length
at the back and make it level.

2121
01:33:24,691 --> 01:33:27,027
WHICH DO YOU PREFER?

2122
01:33:27,694 --> 01:33:29,296
- I think...
- Do you like this?

2123
01:33:29,362 --> 01:33:32,165
Yes, I think either cut will be okay.

2124
01:33:32,632 --> 01:33:33,934
Do you pull your hair
behind your ears?

2125
01:33:34,401 --> 01:33:36,670
- Just on one side.
- Okay.

2126
01:33:37,904 --> 01:33:39,873
They must be having
a fun conversation.

2127
01:33:42,209 --> 01:33:44,211
They must be having
a fun conversation.

2128
01:33:45,545 --> 01:33:47,247
If you see here, I use

2129
01:33:47,314 --> 01:33:50,417
coral or pink shades for makeup.

2130
01:33:50,484 --> 01:33:53,120
I had this cushion foundation,
and it was so...

2131
01:33:53,186 --> 01:33:55,789
It was so glossy it made my face
look almost shiny.

2132
01:33:56,223 --> 01:33:57,757
- I wondered...
- I use this, too.

2133
01:33:57,824 --> 01:34:00,293
- I have this, too.
- Do you really? No way.

2134
01:34:00,360 --> 01:34:02,028
And to be honest, I like ducks.

2135
01:34:02,095 --> 01:34:05,098
- What, for real?
- This is a collab with a duck.

2136
01:34:05,432 --> 01:34:07,100
I HAVE ONE HERE

2137
01:34:07,367 --> 01:34:08,368
DROPPING WITH A CRASH

2138
01:34:08,435 --> 01:34:09,669
Are you okay?

2139
01:34:09,736 --> 01:34:11,171
Are you two okay?

2140
01:34:12,672 --> 01:34:14,541
- I bought it because I like ducks.
- Did you really?

2141
01:34:14,608 --> 01:34:15,609
- No way.
- Yes.

2142
01:34:15,675 --> 01:34:17,144
- It's so pretty.
- Isn't it?

2143
01:34:17,210 --> 01:34:18,378
It's totally what I like.

2144
01:34:19,146 --> 01:34:20,247
I use this, too.

2145
01:34:20,313 --> 01:34:21,381
- Do you really use this?
- Yes.

2146
01:34:21,448 --> 01:34:22,716
- I use this.
- Gosh.

2147
01:34:22,782 --> 01:34:24,217
- Really?
- We use a lot of the same stuff.

2148
01:34:24,851 --> 01:34:26,153
- I use that.
- It's widely loved.

2149
01:34:26,219 --> 01:34:28,488
- It gives you a sharper look.
- Does it?

2150
01:34:28,555 --> 01:34:29,556
It has that effect.

2151
01:34:30,423 --> 01:34:31,491
- Under the chin.
- Like that?

2152
01:34:32,125 --> 01:34:33,827
That's how many people use it.

2153
01:34:34,327 --> 01:34:38,765
MEANWHILE, IN THE SHAMPOO ROOM

2154
01:34:40,100 --> 01:34:41,434
I'll wash your hair now.

2155
01:34:46,940 --> 01:34:49,109
SPREADING THE SHAMPOO EVENLY

2156
01:34:49,543 --> 01:34:52,212
RUBBING

2157
01:34:52,479 --> 01:34:53,780
I like the smell.

2158
01:34:53,847 --> 01:34:55,982
- It smells nice, doesn't it?
- Yes.

2159
01:34:56,516 --> 01:34:59,686
- It's really cool on my scalp.
- Good.

2160
01:35:01,821 --> 01:35:05,425
It prevents too much hair
from falling out

2161
01:35:05,492 --> 01:35:10,597
and also strengthens
the thinning hair.

2162
01:35:10,664 --> 01:35:12,432
- Oh, really?
- Yes.

2163
01:35:13,767 --> 01:35:17,003
- You're starting 12th grade soon.
- Yes.

2164
01:35:17,137 --> 01:35:18,638
You must have lots of concerns

2165
01:35:18,705 --> 01:35:21,107
and get stressed
even when you don't need to.

2166
01:35:21,174 --> 01:35:24,144
That happens just because
you're getting ready for college.

2167
01:35:24,211 --> 01:35:27,414
But it's hard for everybody.

2168
01:35:27,781 --> 01:35:30,650
So I think I can get through it.

2169
01:35:31,051 --> 01:35:32,953
Because it's not hard just for you?

2170
01:35:33,019 --> 01:35:36,256
- It's equally hard for everyone.
- You're right.

2171
01:35:36,790 --> 01:35:40,427
I hope your road to university
is free of stress.

2172
01:35:40,493 --> 01:35:42,996
SHE FEELS REASSURED

2173
01:35:45,065 --> 01:35:46,766
VROOM

2174
01:35:47,434 --> 01:35:50,337
A MOTORCYCLE PASSES THE BARBERSHOP

2175
01:35:51,671 --> 01:35:53,907
TURNING IN

2176
01:35:53,974 --> 01:35:56,676
PARKING RIGHT OUTSIDE

2177
01:35:56,743 --> 01:35:58,545
STRIDING IN

2178
01:35:58,612 --> 01:36:00,981
- Hello.
- Hello.

2179
01:36:01,047 --> 01:36:02,449
- Welcome.
- Hi.

2180
01:36:02,515 --> 01:36:03,783
- Hello.
- Hello.

2181
01:36:04,184 --> 01:36:06,953
IS IT ANOTHER CUSTOMER?

2182
01:36:07,387 --> 01:36:08,521
GYU-RI SMILES SHYLY?

2183
01:36:08,588 --> 01:36:10,156
- I'm here for Gyu-ri.
- He's her father.

2184
01:36:10,223 --> 01:36:12,325
- Oh, really? Gosh.
- Yes.

2185
01:36:12,392 --> 01:36:14,761
GYU-RI'S FATHER CAME FOR HER

2186
01:36:15,295 --> 01:36:17,397
- Is this my daughter?
- It's Gyu-ri.

2187
01:36:18,665 --> 01:36:20,533
What? How did you get so pretty?

2188
01:36:21,534 --> 01:36:24,704
UNLIKE HIS QUIET DAUGHTER,
HE'S FULL OF ENERGY

2189
01:36:25,505 --> 01:36:27,007
That haircut...

2190
01:36:27,073 --> 01:36:28,475
- What's this?
- I'm getting a manicure.

2191
01:36:28,541 --> 01:36:30,243
You two are here as well?

2192
01:36:30,844 --> 01:36:32,445
- You came with her?
- Yes.

2193
01:36:32,512 --> 01:36:34,314
We came here with Gyu-ri.

2194
01:36:34,781 --> 01:36:37,284
- These look tasty.
- They made us fish-shaped buns.

2195
01:36:37,350 --> 01:36:38,918
- Did they?
- You can have some.

2196
01:36:38,985 --> 01:36:40,086
- May I?
- Yes.

2197
01:36:40,153 --> 01:36:41,655
- It's really good.
- Yes.

2198
01:36:41,721 --> 01:36:44,791
- I had one last time.
- Oh, right.

2199
01:36:44,858 --> 01:36:46,159
- Really?
- He said so.

2200
01:36:46,226 --> 01:36:49,129
- That's how we heard of this place.
- Oh, really?

2201
01:36:49,195 --> 01:36:51,564
I said you served fish-shaped buns
and do your hair.

2202
01:36:52,232 --> 01:36:53,700
- What's inside?
- Custard cream.

2203
01:36:53,767 --> 01:36:55,168
The custard cream one is nice.

2204
01:36:55,235 --> 01:36:57,237
That's the plan right now.

2205
01:36:57,304 --> 01:36:58,305
HE'S LOOKING AT THE MURAL

2206
01:36:58,371 --> 01:37:01,074
The peach...

2207
01:37:01,308 --> 01:37:02,742
They look a bit too...

2208
01:37:03,943 --> 01:37:05,745
- Small and insignificant?
- Yes.

2209
01:37:07,414 --> 01:37:09,282
You did well for a first-time job.

2210
01:37:10,050 --> 01:37:11,618
That's good to hear. Thanks so much.

2211
01:37:11,685 --> 01:37:12,686
HE'S A KIND MAN

2212
01:37:13,186 --> 01:37:17,057
GYU-RI'S GETTING HER HAIR BLOW-DRIED

2213
01:37:17,290 --> 01:37:19,993
THINKING

2214
01:37:20,293 --> 01:37:24,397
Rather than have it stick out,
would it be nicer if it lay flat?

2215
01:37:24,464 --> 01:37:25,565
Yes, nice and straight.

2216
01:37:25,632 --> 01:37:27,000
We're painting it ourselves.

2217
01:37:27,767 --> 01:37:30,837
THE PART-TIMER ACTS LIKE A BIG SISTER
AND RECOMMENDS A STYLE

2218
01:37:31,805 --> 01:37:35,175
THE HAIR AT THE SIDES
WILL BE PULLED STRAIGHT

2219
01:37:36,409 --> 01:37:38,011
It suits her so well.

2220
01:37:40,280 --> 01:37:41,915
Yes, and it's for a good cause.

2221
01:37:43,717 --> 01:37:47,821
ADDING VOLUME TO THE ROOTS

2222
01:37:48,621 --> 01:37:49,856
- Do you like it?
- Yes.

2223
01:37:50,790 --> 01:37:53,193
HER PERSONALIZED BOB IS COMPLETE

2224
01:37:54,094 --> 01:37:57,330
FROM LONG STRAIGHT HAIR

2225
01:37:58,498 --> 01:38:01,835
TO A BOB THAT ACCENTUATES
HER FACIAL FEATURES

2226
01:38:02,001 --> 01:38:03,536
She came to get her hair cut

2227
01:38:03,603 --> 01:38:07,073
and she kept saying
she was too nervous to get it done.

2228
01:38:07,474 --> 01:38:10,176
HOW CAN A PLACE LIKE THIS EVEN EXIST?

2229
01:38:10,410 --> 01:38:11,945
His face was tiny

2230
01:38:12,011 --> 01:38:15,248
and he smiled when he looked at us.

2231
01:38:15,648 --> 01:38:17,384
HEARTS POUNDING

2232
01:38:17,884 --> 01:38:20,286
WHERE WILL YOU DONATE THE HAIR TO?

2233
01:38:20,687 --> 01:38:24,391
I'm donating it
to help children fighting cancer.

2234
01:38:24,457 --> 01:38:29,729
I had it cut so they can
make wigs out of it.

2235
01:38:29,796 --> 01:38:31,231
I love my new style.

2236
01:38:31,297 --> 01:38:33,366
I don't miss my hair at all.

2237
01:38:33,433 --> 01:38:36,302
My hair will keep growing.

2238
01:38:36,369 --> 01:38:39,038
It will keep getting longer anyway.

2239
01:38:39,105 --> 01:38:42,041
It would be meaningful
if it could be used

2240
01:38:42,108 --> 01:38:44,778
to help people
who need it more than I do.

2241
01:38:44,844 --> 01:38:46,479
I don't regret it.

2242
01:38:47,614 --> 01:38:51,918
A NICE PLACE THAT HELPS DO GOOD

2243
01:38:52,986 --> 01:38:55,422
Hello, this is the Village Barber.

2244
01:38:55,488 --> 01:38:58,024
I want a haircut,
so come by around 2.

2245
01:38:58,091 --> 01:38:59,526
Should we try
a house call haircut today?

2246
01:38:59,592 --> 01:39:00,794
A HOUSE CALL?

2247
01:39:00,860 --> 01:39:03,263
Where should we do the haircut?

2248
01:39:03,329 --> 01:39:04,998
Let me move the mirror a bit.

2249
01:39:05,064 --> 01:39:06,399
Over here on this side.

2250
01:39:06,666 --> 01:39:07,934
- Where should I look?
- The left side.

2251
01:39:08,101 --> 01:39:09,235
This side?

2252
01:39:09,302 --> 01:39:10,904
I've still got a long way to go.

2253
01:39:10,970 --> 01:39:11,971
What's going on?

2254
01:39:12,038 --> 01:39:14,073
Boss PARK didn't bring
the cutting cape with him.

2255
01:39:14,140 --> 01:39:15,909
What a fool.
How could I forget the cape?

2256
01:39:16,376 --> 01:39:18,411
I'VE NEVER BEEN ON A HOUSE CALL

2257
01:39:19,212 --> 01:39:20,213
What is that sound?

2258
01:39:20,280 --> 01:39:21,648
Please boil some water.

2259
01:39:21,714 --> 01:39:22,982
I'd like a cup of coffee.

2260
01:39:23,049 --> 01:39:24,083
Where are you headed?

2261
01:39:24,150 --> 01:39:25,351
Come on in. Hurry and have some.

2262
01:39:25,418 --> 01:39:27,687
- Welcome.
- Hello.

2263
01:39:27,754 --> 01:39:29,322
- You're here at last.
- Yes.

2264
01:39:29,389 --> 01:39:31,124
- May I cover your face?
- No need.

2265
01:39:31,191 --> 01:39:33,726
- It's warm, ma'am.
- Oh, thank you.

2266
01:39:33,793 --> 01:39:36,129
- Try saying "hi," Ji-hui.
- Hi.

2267
01:39:36,196 --> 01:39:38,465
I don't see any rice cakes
for the soup.

2268
01:39:38,531 --> 01:39:41,868
FINALLY PASSED OUT

2269
01:39:42,969 --> 01:39:45,371
We know
that tomorrow is the last day.

2270
01:39:45,438 --> 01:39:46,473
THEIR LAST DAY IS COMING NEAR

2271
01:39:46,539 --> 01:39:48,041
I keep getting melancholic.

2272
01:39:48,107 --> 01:39:50,009
- Oh, my goodness.
- Come hang out again.

2273
01:39:50,076 --> 01:39:52,612
We got through January
thanks to Ms. Ou.

2274
01:39:52,679 --> 01:39:55,215
- Take some yogurt with you.
- Oh, my, thank you.

2275
01:39:55,515 --> 01:39:56,816
I can't put it into words.

2276
01:39:57,283 --> 01:39:58,918
It doesn't feel real yet.

2277
01:40:03,156 --> 01:40:04,424
THE VILLAGE BARBER

2278
01:40:11,865 --> 01:40:13,933
THE VILLAGE BARBER

2279
01:40:15,935 --> 01:40:17,937
Subtitles by Eunsook Youn,
Hoyoung Yun, and Jennifer Lim
